title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Reserve stock.
Remove skin and tear into bite size pieces.
Cook spaghetti in stock from chicken. Reserve broth again.
Melt Velveeta cheese in 1/2 stock over low heat, stirring often.
Combine all ingredients except stock.
Mix good.
Add stock so that mixture is little soupy.
Bake, uncovered, in 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Do not cook dry.
Add more stock if needed.
It is easier to blend all if you break spaghetti in half before cooking.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Mix tuna, onion, celery and mayonnaise and set aside.
Cook egg noodles until slightly firm.

title: zucchini bake(microwave)
directions: Place zucchini and onion in 10 x 6 x 2-inch dish.
Cover with plastic wrap, turning one edge back slightly to vent.
Microwave on High 10 minutes.
Drain.
In large bowl, mix together eggs, cheese, salt and pepper.
Add zucchini and onions, stirring well. Grease dish in which vegetables were cooked.
Pour mixture into dish and cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High 6 to 8 minutes until center is set.
Rotate dish 1/2 turn after 6 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: molded carrot salad
directions: Prepare gelatin as stated on package.
When it has set slightly, add other ingredients.
Chill and serve on a crisp lettuce leaf.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine ground beef with all ingredients except cheeses.
Pat ground beef mixture into bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie pan. Bake for 30 minutes.
Drain off fat. Sprinkle with Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
Return to oven for 15 minutes longer.
Slice into wedges and eat!

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Melt butter and add sugar; stir and let dissolve.
Let cool and add eggs.
Mix all ingredients well.
Crush vanilla wafers. Add coconut, pecans and milk, then pour into large bowl and mix all ingredients well.
Oven temperature:
325° for 1 hour 20 minutes.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream shortening,
sugar
and
eggs.
Beat
well
after each. Add
sifted dry ingredients (flour, soda, baking powder and spices alternately
with	buttermilk.
Add
jam, raisins, nuts, grape juice
and vanilla.
Bake in 3 greased and floured 9-inch pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put a little powdered sugar on your hands.
Shape into small balls.
Shake a few times in a bag of powdered sugar.
Store in tin or refrigerator.

title: honey-mustard sauce
directions: Mix together and refrigerate until needed.
Good on meats, poultry and cheese.

title: corn bread stuffing
directions: Melt oleo in a large skillet.
Add onions and celery. Cook until onions are soft.
Remove from heat and place in a bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and seasonings. Toss lightly to combine. Makes about 4 cups.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding mix and milk. Beat. Add Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip. Mix well.

title: pork stir-fry with blue cheese
directions: Partially freeze meat and thinly slice across grain; set aside.
For sauce, combine next 4 ingredients.
Preheat wok and stir-fry veggies in oil.
Transfer to dish.
Stir-fry 1/2 meat at a time, then set aside.
Add water and sauce to wok.
Stir until thickened, scraping bottom.
Stir in meat and tomato until heated and spoon over veggies.
Top with extra Blue cheese.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, taco mix and olives.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles.
Shape triangles in ungreased 9 x 10-inch pie pan, pressing up the sides to form a crust.
Sprinkle 1 cup corn chips over bottom of crust; fill with meat mixture; spread sour cream over meat.
Cover with cheese.
Sprinkle remaining corn chips over top.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes, until crust is golden brown.
Serve in wedges, topped with lettuce and tomatoes.
Salsa on the side.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cook onions in butter until lightly browned, about 15 minutes. Add beef broth, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Sprinkle sliced hard rolls or French bread generously with Parmesan cheese.
Broil until lightly browned.
Float atop each serving of soup.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate milk shake
directions: Place milk and syrup in blender.
Cover and blend on high speed 2 seconds.
Add ice cream.
Cover and blend on low speed about 5 seconds longer or until smooth.
Makes 2 servings.

title: taco salad
directions: Make a large salad with lettuce, tomatoes, onion, olives and carrots; toss well.
Pour in Ranch Style beans (juice and all). Add cheese and mix well.
Pour Fritos over all.
Add 1/2 bottle Russian dressing (small bottle).
Mix all and enjoy.

title: white christmas pie
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cold water in a saucepan.

Let stand 1 minute. Add 1/4 cup sugar, flour, salt and milk. Cook over low heat, stirring until the gelatin dissolves and mixture is hot. Remove from heat and chill until the consistency of unbeaten egg white. Add vanilla and almond extracts.
Beat at medium speed with an electric mixer until smooth. Combine fruit and powdered sugar, tossing to coat.
Set aside. Beat whipping cream until foamy. Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar, beating until soft peaks form.
Fold fruit mixture, whipping cream and 1 cup coconut into gelatin mixture. Spoon into pastry shell. Sprinkle with remaining coconut. Chill 8 hours.

title: nacho chip dip
directions: Soften the cream cheese.
Smooth into bottom of casserole dish.
Cover with onions.
Cover with chili.
Cover with grated cheese.
Heat in microwave until cheese melts and bubbles.
Serve with tortilla or nacho chips.
Recipe easily doubles.

title: banana chocolate loaf
directions: Cream together the butter or margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add the eggs and salt and mix well.
Dissolve the baking powder and baking soda in the sour cream and add to the creamed mixture.
Stir in the banana pulp.
Gradually add the flour, vanilla and the chocolate chips.
Pour into well-greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix warm water with sugar and 2 packages of yeast.
Mix until dissolved.
Mix in salt and flour.
Knead like biscuit dough.
Pat dough into a rectangle and let rest for ten minutes.
Cut rolls with a biscuit cutter and place on an oiled 9x13 pan.
Let rise for 2 hours, then bake 10 to 12 minutes in a preheated 400 degree oven. These are both easy and delicious.

title: southwestern frito dip
directions: Mix together and let mixture set in refrigerator before serving.
Serve with large Frito scoops.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, brown sugar and butter. Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until butter is melted and sugar has dissolved, 6 to 8 minutes.
In a large mixing bowl, combine cooked mixture with ice cream. Beat at medium speed, scraping bowl often until smooth, 1 to 2 minutes.

title: cherry nut bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add with juice and cherries and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in small loaf pans filled a little over half full.

title: quick beef and bean tacos
directions: In medium skillet, cook beef and onion until beef is browned. Drain off Fat. Add soup and water. Reduce heat to low, cove rand simmer 5 minutes. Divide meat mixture among taco shells. Top with cheese, lettuce, tomatoes and sour cream.

title: cheesy breakfast casserole(makes 12 servings.  prep time:  20 minutes.)
directions: In a large skillet, prepare hash browns according to package directions. Sprinkle with garlic salt and pepper. Transfer to a large greased baking dish. Top with soup. Sprinkle half of the meat over soup.

title: two-crust lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Blend in butter, add beaten eggs, water, rind and lemon (cut into slices) to sugar mixture. Put in unbaked pie shell.
Top with crust and pick with fork.
No slits in top.
Filling will be real sugary.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: dog biscuits
directions: In a small bowl, combine baking yeast and warm water, keep stirring until dissolved.
Add chicken or beef broth.
Mix together flours, brewer's yeast, powdered milk, bulgur, corn meal, parsley flakes and garlic.
Add liquid to mixture.
Dough will be stiff.
(Add more stock if you must.)

title: easy drop a p's
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg.
Sift in dry ingredients and mix well.
Put in balls the size of a walnut.
Flatten with fork or fingers on baking sheet.
Sprinkle with colored sugar if desired.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are golden brown.

title: gourmet pork chops
directions: Sprinkle chops with salt and pepper. Dredge in flour.
Brown in hot oil over medium heat.
Drain.
Place in casserole.
Set aside.
Stir onion and garlic into drippings.
Cook.
Add wine and stock.
Simmer 3 to 5 minutes.
Saute mushrooms in butter.
Add mushrooms, thyme and bay leaf to skillet.
Pour wine sauce over chips.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.

title: chicken and spaghetti casserole
directions: Boil, bone and dice chicken.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth. In separate pot, saute onion and pepper in oleo.
Add to chicken and spaghetti.
Next add rest of ingredients.
Warm all ingredients in oven for 20 or 30 minutes.
Serves 5 to 6 people.

title: quick strawberry trifle
directions: Fold 1/2 cup sugar into sliced strawberries.
Set aside. Beat remaining sugar into cream cheese.
Whip cream.
Fold into cream cheese mixture.
Cut cake into slices about 1/3-inch thick. Arrange a layer of slices in a bowl.
Put a layer of berries and a layer of cream.
Continue layering, ending with cream.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: coffee-basted lamb
directions: Rub salt and pepper over the surface of the lamb and bake in a moderate 350° oven (180° C) for 1 hour.
Mix the coffee, cream and sugar and pour over the lamb.
Continue cooking for the remainder of the cooking time, calculated at 30 minutes per pound (60 minutes per 1 kg.), basting frequently.
Add a little water if the liquid evaporates too much during cooking.
When cooked, remove the lamb; skim off fat from the pan, putting aside 2 tablespoons of fat in the saucepan.
Stir in the flour and cook for 1 minute. Add enough water to the roasting pan to make 2 cups of liquid; stir well, lifting off any baked on juices.
Heat the fat in the saucepan, stir in the flour and cook for 1 minute.
Add the liquid from the roasting pan and stir until the sauce thickens and boils. Add the currant jelly and stir until jelly is completely absorbed.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pound chicken breasts to same width to prevent uneven cooking.
Spray 2-quart casserole dish with Pam. Arrange breasts in casserole, add salt, pepper and Accent.
Cover breasts with sliced onions, peppers and mushrooms.
Add lemon juice.
In a small bowl, mix soup with 1/2 can water; use more if you would like a gravy.
Pour over ingredients and top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Cover and bake for 1 hour.

title: onion baked pork chops
directions: Mix soup mix and bread crumbs.
Dip pork chops in beaten egg, then in bread crumb mixture.
Place in lightly greased shallow pan.
Bake, turning once, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sparkling lemonade
directions: Place lemonade concentrate in pitcher. Add ginger ale and mix. Slice lemon. Add lemons and raspberries to juice mixture. Serve over ice.

title: sweet and sour salad dressing
directions: Mix in blender, then add 1 cup and 3 tablespoons vinegar and 3 cups and 3 tablespoons oil.
Mix well again.
Let stand for 1 or 2 days before serving.
Refrigerate.

title: 6 layer dinner
directions: Layer
ingredients
in
order given in deep dish casserole. Bake 2 hours in a 350° oven, covered.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour the butter into the pan.
Mix above ingredients and pour over the butter.
Spoon the peaches over the top, and sprinkle more sugar over the top.
Bake for 1 hour at 325 degrees.

title: blueberry nut bread
directions: Turn into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes.

title: travis's beef stroganoff
directions: In a large frying pan, brown beef in butter.
Remove from pan. Add onion and cook until golden brown.
Remove from pan.
Blend flour into butter.
Add consomme and seasonings.
Stir until gravy is smooth.
Add sour cream.
Place noodles in bottom of a large casserole.
Cover with mushrooms, onion, beef and then gravy. Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: texas quick candy
directions: Boil sugar and Karo for only 1 minute.	Take off heat and add peanut butter.
Pour over cereal.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add and mix well, oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Add and mix well, flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and baking powder.
Add chopped nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: aunt donnah's roast possum
directions: After you kill the possum be careful not to let him get away. While you're talking and planning how you're going to eat him, he's going to be slipping right from under your nose.
All he was doing was playing possum.
Skin him and clean him before you go another foot, then the mess is gone and he won't get away.
When you get him home, rub salt and pepper all over his body, then run a mixture of vinegar and brown sugar over the salt and pepper.
Wrap up the possum in a good baking pan and let it stand in the refrigerator overnight.
The next morning put the pan with the possum still in it (hopefully) on top of stove.
Add 2 or 3 spoons of bacon fat and sear him on all sides.
Then add chopped onions (2 of them).
Put in the oven and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Pull him out and roll him over and now you can add your sweet potatoes (just surround him with 'em).
Put back in the oven and bake for another 1 1/2 hours or until he is tender and juicy.

title: graham cracker crumb crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add melted butter.
Line the bottom and sides of pan. Do not bake.

title: sweet scents
directions: Place peels from fruit, cloves and cinnamon in a pan of water. Let this simmer several hours and it will fill the house with a wonderful aroma.
By adding more water when needed, this batch can be used for 2 or 3 days, then you may start all over again with a fresh batch.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix together the melted oleo and crushed graham crackers into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Beat together the powdered sugar, oleo, vanilla and eggs for 15 minutes until light; spread over graham crackers.
Spread drained crushed pineapple over top.
Layer bananas on pineapple mixture.
Top with Cool Whip; garnish with cherries and nuts.
Chill overnight.

title: anita's taco dip
directions: Layer in order as given.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: baked beans
directions: Open can of beans and pour in saucepan.
Add all ingredients, except bacon.
Cook over slow heat until well blended and butter is melted.
Cook bacon in microwave until crisp.
Pour beans in casserole dish.
Lay or crumble bacon on top of beans.
Bake in oven at 300° for about 1 hour.
If in a hurry, just simmer in saucepan about 30 minutes instead of baking.

title: stuffed banana peppers
directions: Clean peppers and split down sides. Drop into boiling water for 3 minutes. Brown hamburger and onions; add salt and chili powder. Add cheese to mixture until melted. Fill peppers and wrap in crescent rolls. Bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion until done, drain grease.
Mix in green chiles and 1/4 c. cheese.
Put 1/3 to 1/2 c. meat mixture onto each tortilla and roll up.
Mix soups and enchilada sauce until smooth.
Put a small amount in bottom of baking dish.
Place tortilla in dish, cover with remaining sauce.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Beat the egg whites until stiff.
Add 1/2 of the brown sugar and continue to beat to blend, then add the other half and the vanilla and continue to blend.
When all is added and stiff, stir in the pecans.
Drop by teaspoon onto a brown paper bag on cookie sheet and bake at 275° for 1 hour.

title: sugar-free strawberry pie
directions: Make crust.
(To make sugar free, add butter and add cinnamon to graham crackers - no sugar.)
Place in freezer until ready to use.
In medium saucepan, combine Jell-O, pop and cornstarch. Heat until all ingredients are dissolved and thickened.
Slice strawberries.
Make sure they are completely drained.
Add to liquid.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate.
Makes 1 pie.

title: chicken fruit salad
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients, except whipped cream. Just before serving, fold in whipped cream.
Makes 6 one cup servings.

title: seven vegetable salad
directions: Use any amounts desired; dice in bowl and add Italian dressing.
Best if made the night before.

title: hungry jack hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet and drain.
Add next 5 ingredients and let it come to a bubbly boil.
Pour in casserole dish.
Cut biscuits in half and place around edge of dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: autumn soup
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Simmer everything listed for 3 hours, then take out pork hocks, discard skin, fat and bones.
Cut up meat and return to soup.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix and chill.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: rice lentil pilaf
directions: Combine all ingredients. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low. Simmer, covered, 45 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix together.
Grease skillet or pan.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mashed potato salad
directions: Mash cooked potatoes well.
Add chopped onions, pickles, celery salt and salt.
Combine well as you add salad dressing and cooked eggs.
Refrigerate promptly.
Serves 12.

title: clam spread
directions: Combine clams with juice of 1 lemon, onion, green pepper, butter, garlic, parsley flakes, oregano and cayenne pepper. Simmer until onion and green pepper are soft.
Add bread crumbs. Place in a shallow baking dish (pie plate is good).
Dot with Parmesan and Cheddar cheeses.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Serve with Matso.

title: noralene stock's coconut icing
directions: Cream together margarine, flour and sugar.
Add milk and boil under slow heat until creamy.
Add coconut (1/4 to 1/2 cup) and nuts as desired.
Add vanilla.
Cool and ice cake.

title: boozie dogs
directions: Slice each wiener into 6 pieces and set aside.
Combine catsup, brown sugar and bourbon.
Simmer slowly 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add wieners to sauce and simmer 45 minutes longer.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Mix vanilla pudding and milk according to directions.
Set aside.
Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip together.
Add to pudding. Break Oreo cookies into pieces.
Pour butter on cookies.
Mix some of the cookies into creamed mixture.
Put mixture into serving bowl.
Top with most of the broken pieces of cookies.

title: new york spaghetti pie
directions: Break spaghetti in half
and
cook
in
boiling, salted water, just until tender;
drain.
In a medium bowl, beat eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Add
warm
spaghetti
and
toss
to mix. Line a buttered 10-inch pie plate with the spaghetti mixture.

title: artichoke and crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes until hot and bubbly and top is slightly browned.
Serve with corn chips or crackers.

title: mark's chili
directions: Mix tomato sauce, tomato paste, tomato soup, kidney beans (do not drain), sugar and chili
powder into large pot.
Put burner on low heat, stirring occasionally. Brown ground beef draining off as much grease as you can.
Add meat to sauce and let simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: hawaiian yams
directions: Mix the potato mixture.
Put in a baking dish.
Make sure there is room for the topping.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sauce bearnaise
directions: Reduce by boiling vinegar, wine, shallots and tarragon to 2 tablespoons.
Strain and incorporate into Hollandaise with parsley.
Makes 2 cups.

title: strawberry angel dessert
directions: In a saucepan put water and Knox gelatine.
Let stand 5 minutes to soften.
Let strawberries thaw.
Heat and stir gelatine over low heat just until it dissolves.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in undrained thawed berries.
Chill until partially thick.
Fold in whipped topping.
Cut cake portion into cubes.
Place in large bowl.
Pour strawberry mix over cake and mix gently.
Pour into 8-inch square Pyrex pan.
Chill until firm. Garnish with fresh berries if you wish.
Serves 9.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix this all together well. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Cream margarine; gradually add sugar, beating well until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Combine flour and salt; add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Add pecans.

title: slow cooker barbecued brisket
directions: Sprinkle brisket with garlic powder, celery salt, onion powder and liquid smoke.
Place in oven-cooking bag.
Seal bag.
Pierce bag once.
Place in slow cooker.
Cook on low for 13 to 18 hours.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients, make a hole in center and pour in all liquid ingredients.
Mix all thoroughly by hand.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease casserole dish.
Cook rice.
Put in casserole dish.
In a pan, add cream of chicken soup, onion soup mix, water and butter.
Cook until all ingredients are mixed.
Put chicken on top of rice and add ingredients from pan.
Cook, covered, with foil for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, cocoa and salt into saucepan.
Slowly stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring all the time until mixture thickens.
Stir and cook 3 minutes longer.
Stir in vanilla.
Serve over hot biscuits.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Whip pudding and milk until blended.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Chill 20 minutes.
Spread on remainder of whipped topping (2 cups whipped).
Chill overnight.

title: double chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine pie filling, milk, butter and chips in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full bubbling boil.
Remove from heat and cool 5 minutes.
Stir twice and pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Into a glass 9 x 12-inch pan, put ingredients in order, in layers.
Do not combine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: filled apricot cookies
directions: Mix sugar, flour, baking powder, soda and butter like pie crumbs.
Then beat the eggs in a cup and fill the cup with milk. Cook apricots until soft and add sugar or honey to sweeten.
Let cool and spread one side of cookie with filling and top with other cookie dough.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: italian sesame cookies
directions: Fill a bowl 1/4 with milk; put aside.
Fill a bowl 1/4 with sesame seed; put aside.
Mix all remaining ingredients in a large bowl until it becomes a good consistency for molding.

title: french fried onions
directions: Slice
onions
in 1/2 inch rounds.
Separate each ring, using the
largest ones.
Soak for 1 hour in sweet milk.
Mix flour, salt,
oil
and
water
until smooth.
Fold in stiffly beaten
egg white.
Dry
onion slices.
Dip in batter and fry until a golden brown and the onion is tender.

title: oven pot roast(this is an original)
directions: Brown steak in hot oil in skillet until both sides are medium brown.
Place meat in large baking pan.
Add concentrated soup and fill up each soup can again with water.
Pour over meat.
Add bay leaves, salt and pepper and sliced onions to pan.
Cover tightly and cook for 1 hour.

title: easy swiss steak
directions: Trim all
fat
from
meat
and	cut
in serving pieces. Pound to	tenderize.
Fry
meat in shortening until brown.
Do not salt meat.
Mix	together the gravy mix and dry onion soup mix.	Place 1
layer
of meat in pan and sprinkle with half of the dry mixture.
Add remaining meat and sprinkle with remaining gravy and onion soup mix.
Pour 2 1/2 cups water over and cover tightly. Bake at 325° for 3 hours.

title: meat loaf
directions: Soak bread in milk until it soaks up all it will hold.
Mix bread, ground beef, onion, salt, egg and half of tomato paste. Shape into loaf.
Top with rest of paste and bacon strips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: microwave corn-on-the-cob
directions: Husk corn.
Rinse well.
Roll each ear of corn in 1 paper towel.
Seal tightly.
Cook in microwave on High, allowing 3 minutes for each ear.
(Do not dry corn before wrapping.)

title: carrot casserole
directions: Melt butter and cheese together. Pour over the carrots. Sprinkle with Ritz crackers, crumbled.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: brisket
directions: Place brisket in large cooking bag.
Sprinkle contents of soup mix and pour on liquid smoke over brisket.
Close bag and puncture holes in top.
Place in large roasting pan and cook at 250° for 8 hours.
(It cooks while I sleep.)

title: sicilian meat roll
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients.
Add the ground beef and mix. On foil, pat meat out to a 10 x 12-inch rectangle.
Arrange slices of ham on top.
Cover with the shredded Mozzarella cheese. Starting from wide end, carefully roll up meat, using foil to lift. Place, seam side down, in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Cut sliced Mozzarella cheese diagonally; place on top of meat roll and return to oven until it is melted.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook the spaghetti in boiling salted water and drain when cooked thoroughly.
Set aside.
Saute the beef in 1 1/4 teaspoons butter until brown.
Add tomato sauce with salt and pepper.
If you use a commercial tomato sauce, add 1 teaspoon chopped basil, 1 teaspoon oregano and 1 tablespoon parsley in addition.
Mix well with meat and let simmer for 10 minutes.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Crush cookies, add cool whip. Kid's can make this.

title: hedy's icebox cinnamon sweet rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in scalded milk, sugar, oil, baking powder, salt, eggs and 2 to 3 cups flour.
Beat together until smooth.
Continue to mix remaining flour until dough is easy to handle.

title: molded green salad
directions: Mix jello with hot water.
Let cool and thicken, almost jell. Add the balance of the ingredients.
Include horseradish if you like it; stir well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan or leave in a casserole dish.
Refrigerate to set.
May be cut into squares and served on lettuce or left in a casserole and passed.

title: scotch-a-roos
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup in a 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil; remove from heat.
Blend in peanut butter and cereal. Pour mixture into buttered cookie sheet.
Spread smooth.
Allow to cool.

title: microwave tater tot casserole
directions: Place melted butter in casserole dish.
Stir in onion and saute.
Combine other ingredients except spices.
Sprinkle spices on top.
Bake in microwave 12 to 15 minutes.

title: stuffed olives
directions: Clean fresh mushrooms. Simmer mushrooms in 1/4 pound butter with small chopped onion for 3 minutes. Add a bottle of cooking sherry and simmer about 5 minutes to heat through. Serve warm.

title: swiss-style fried chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in small bowl.
Combine egg and milk in a second bowl.
Combine next 5 ingredients in a third bowl. Dip fillets in flour, shake off excess.
Dip in egg, then crumb mixture.
Press crumbs on firmly.
Heat margarine in skillet on medium heat.
Pan fry fillets until golden, about 2 minutes on each side.

title: angel food cake strawberry dessert
directions: Line bottom of large baking dish with cake pieces.
Stir boiling water into gelatin in medium bowl for 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Stir in cold water.
Pour over cake pieces. Top with strawberries, reserving several for garnish, if desired. Pour milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire wise for 1 minute.
Spread evenly over cake pieces and strawberries. Let stand for 5 minutes.
Spread whipped topping over pudding. Refrigerate for 4 hours or until set.
Garnish with reserved strawberries.

title: no bake blueberry cheese pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in condensed milk.
Add 1/3 cup lemon juice and vanilla. Pour into crust.
In medium saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Mix well.
Add water and remaining lemon juice.
Add blueberries.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 3 minutes or until thick and clear.
Cool 10 minutes.
Spread over pie. Chill 3 hours until set.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: fruit bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan with aluminum foil.
Spray with nonstick cooking spray; set aside.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking powder and salt. Stir in chopped fruit.
Add eggs, oil and orange juice.
Stir until well blended.
Spread batter into foil-lined pan.
Sprinkle sunflower seeds evenly over top.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Lift foil by ends onto cutting board.
Fold back edges of foil and cut into 3 x 1-inch bars.
Wrap individually in foil and freeze.
Makes 24 bars.

title: sausage potato stew
directions: Cut sausage into 1-inch pieces.
Put in large pot with 1 cup of water and boil until water evaporates and sausage browns in its own grease.
Add onion and saute 1 or 2 minutes.
Add potatoes and 5 cups of water.
Season with salt, pepper and parsley flakes to taste.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for about 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Serve over rice.

title: strawberry cream squares
directions: Dissolve
gelatin
in
boiling
water
and
add
frozen strawberries.
Stir
occasionally until thawed.
Add pineapple and diced bananas.
Pour half in 8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 11-inch pan. Chill until firm.
Spread
sour cream evenly over layer. Carefully ladle remaining
semi-set jello on top.
Chill until firm.

title: southern corn bread
directions: Mix all together and bake until brown at 350°.

title: brunch mary
directions: Mix all above ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or bake for 25 minutes in 350° oven, freeze, then bake 25 minutes in 350° oven day of serving.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: baked fish
directions: Thaw fish, if frozen.
Cut in servings.
Melt butter.
Add lemon juice and onion to butter.
Mix.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes. Dip fish in to cover all over.
Arrange fish in a greased foil-lined shallow pan.
Pour remaining mixture over fish.
(May be seasoned with salt and pepper, if desired.)
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake until fish flakes with a fork.
Cooking time:
25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Place in long baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: marble cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat together the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in the eggs.
Stir in the flour and combine all the ingredients to form a soft ball.
Add the chocolate and gently stir through to give a marble effect.
Wrap the dough in a plastic bag and chill in the refrigerator for 30 minutes.

title: chicken breast in fillo (phyllo) dough
directions: Spread mustard on both sides of chicken.
Spread margarine on one sheet of phyllo.
Place second sheet of phyllo on top of first and spread with margarine.
Place breast half in one corner of phyllo.
Fold corner over breast, then fold sides over and roll breast up in sheets to form a package.
Place in large, ungreased baking dish.
Repeat with remaining breasts and phyllo sheets. Brush packets with margarine.
At this point, the dish may be tightly sealed and frozen.
Thaw completely before baking.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until golden.
Serve hot.

title: squash and raisin pie
directions: Prick the bottom and sides of prepared pie shell.
Bake in a 400° oven until golden.
Make sure the squash is mashed.
Mix squash with remaining ingredients.
Pour into hot pie shell.
Dust with cinnamon and serve with a green vegetable or tossed salad for main dish.

title: easy hors d'oeuvre
directions: Mix all together and let stand for at least 20 minutes.
Can be made the day before.
Serve with party rye or stoned wheat thins.

title: sweet sour pickles
directions: Boil water, vinegar, salt and sugar.
Pour over cucumbers that have been packed with dill in quart jar.
Seal.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs; beat.
Sift flour, cocoa, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add flour and milk.
Beat well.
Add boiling water.
Beat until smooth.
Bake at 350°.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Drain pineapple.
Save juice.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Shred or chop vegetables.
Heat oil in pan or wok.
To hot oil, add chicken, a little at a time, fry fast until browned.
Add vegetables.
Do same as chicken until tender.
Add pineapple.
To make sauce:
Mix juice, sugar, vinegar, soy sauce, paste and ginger.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Pour over mixture and simmer for 10 minutes or until done.

title: artichoke pasta salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients; toss gently.
Serve chilled, if desired.
Makes 4 (1 1/2 cup) servings.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix thoroughly and chill several hours.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Put enough oil in frying pan to cook hash browns and onion together.
When brown, set aside.
Cook sausage.
Scramble the sausage until done and then drain grease from sausage.
Return and combine in frying pan potatoes, onion and sausage and then break eggs over top and scramble into mixture.
Add 1 1/4 cups of grated cheese to mixture.
Pour into casserole dish and put remaining cheese on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 15 to 20 minutes until cheese melts.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken, then cut up.
Put in 2-quart greased casserole dish.
Mix chicken soup with milk.
Pour over chicken.
Then add 1 cup broth to stuffing mix; spread over top of casserole.
Bake in 350° oven about 45 minutes.

title: 8 - 8 - 8 dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill.
Recipe can be doubled.
Serve with Fritos.

title: amish casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add tomato soup, catsup, water, salt and brown sugar.
Simmer; stir frequently.
Cook noodles by package directions while sauce simmers.
Drain noodles and mix with sour cream and chicken soup.
Pour noodle mixture into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Slice Velveeta layer on top of noodles. Pour sauce on top of cheese.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake another 20 to 30 minutes.

title: flaky pastry
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture is coarse and granular.
Mix vinegar and egg to ice water.
Add a little at a time, tossing the flour mixture with a fork until all particles are moistened.
Do not knead, but press into a ball. Store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Makes 4 pie shells.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, eggs, buttermilk and vegetable oil. Add enough water to make a soft batter.
(Note:
Buttermilk makes the batter fluffy so add water to get the batter to the right consistency.)
Cook batter in 8-inch skillet (greased or sprayed) in the oven at 400° until browned.
Turn out of pan to cool.
In large bowl, combine cornbread, torn into small pieces, with buns. Salt and pepper to taste.
Add celery, onions and eggs mashed finely.
Add enough broth to make soft batter.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch dish.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Mix ingredients and pour into dish.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for approximately 50 minutes.
Drizzle with mixture of 10x sugar and lemon juice.

title: graham cracker bars
directions: Break
graham
crackers
where	they
are marked, using enough graham
crackers to fill cookie sheet.
Boil together, over low heat, margarine and sugar, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes.

title: how to cook okra
directions: Heat
oven
Slice okra crossways.
Put oil in skillet
and get hot.
Bread okra with cornmeal and put in hot grease.
Salt to taste and stir okra in the oil and set in hot oven.
Let brown, stirring occasionally, until done.

title: pineapple surprise
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour 2 cans pineapple with juice in pans.
Spread evenly.
Sprinkle yellow cake mix over pineapple. Melt butter and pour over cake mix.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Refrigerate overnight.
Top with Cool Whip to serve.

title: tis and taint
directions: In skillet, brown ground chuck until color changes and meat is crumbled.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook noodles per directions and drain.

title: seafood cocktail sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Serve with chilled cooked shrimp or crab cakes.
Makes 1 cup.

title: sandy's chippy chicken
directions: Line a cookie sheet with aluminum.
Melt oleo in saucepan. Smash up potato chips.
Dip chicken in oleo, then roll in chips. Place on cookie sheet; bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: complete breakfast casserole for 8
directions: Place 3 slices bread in buttered baking dish.
Cover with ham and cheese.
Add remaining bread slices.
Mix the next 4 ingredients together; pour over bread.
Refrigerate overnight. Top with cornflakes.
Drizzle 1 stick of melted oleo over the cornflakes.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.
Serves 8.

title: yellow punch
directions: Pour 4 cups sugar and 1
large jello in pan; add 4 cups water and bring to a
boil.
Let	cool
and add other ingredients. Serves 32.	To change color, substitute another jello.

title: husband's delight
directions: Brown ground beef and drain; add spaghetti sauce to meat.
Stir in Ragu.
Simmer for several minutes; set aside.
Add egg noodles to boiling water and boil until tender.
Drain in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Layer 1/2 noodles, 1/2 ground beef mixture, 1/2 sour cream and 1/2 shredded Cheddar cheese.
Repeat.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 4 servings (can be doubled).

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix crust ingredients together and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: broccoli 'n cheez
directions: Saute onion in margarine and grease a 9 x 13-inch pan or large casserole.
Combine all the ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: strawberry valentine salad
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Blend in small amount of stiffly beaten cream.
Roll cream cheese into the remainder of whipped cream. Mix other ingredients.
Put in heart-shaped mold.
Freeze until firm.
Let stand about 3 minutes to thaw.
Serve on lettuce.
One recipe serves about 10.

title: rocky road candies
directions: Slowly melt chocolate bars in saucepan over medium heat. Remove from heat. Stir in marshmallows, coconut and walnuts. Drop by rounded spoonfuls onto cookie sheet lined with waxed paper. Refrigerate until firm.

title: banana bran muffins
directions: Measure all six dry ingredients into a mixing bowl.
Stir to combine.
Make a well in the center.
Cream butter, sugar and 1 egg until well blended.
Beat in second egg.
Mix into sour milk and bananas.
Pour all at once into well.
Mix until moistened.
Ignore the lumps!
Fill greased muffin pans 3/4 full.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: cinnamon spiced muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine flour, 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder, salt, nutmeg, coriander and allspice.
Combine milk, 1/3 cup melted butter and egg.
Stir milk mixture into flour mixture until well moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin cups.
Bake 10 to 13 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Combine 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Dip tops of muffins into remaining butter and then cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Serve warm.
These also freeze well.

title: beef noodle soup
directions: In a large kettle, place 2 quarts water, the beef, chopped onions and chopped celery.
Season to taste.
Cook until beef is tender; then remove beef from kettle.
Add tomatoes that have been chopped fine and the chopped parsley.
Add 2 quarts water and cook for 20 minutes.
Then drop homemade noodles in while liquid is boiling rapidly.
Cover and cook until noodles are done, about 30 minutes.
Drop beef back in kettle to heat before serving.

title: potato cakes
directions: Shape about 6 balls of potatoes in palms of hands.
Roll in flour to cover both sides.
Heat butter or margarine in skillet over medium heat.
Brown on both sides.

title: meat with red chili
directions: Cut beef into small pieces.
Cook in pan with small amount of oil.
Cook until medium rare.
Add tomatoes, chilies and garlic into blender.
Add to meat.
Add 1 cup of water or 2 to thicken . Add flour and let boil for 15 minutes on low heat.

title: 1932 angel food cake
directions: Beat egg whites frothy.
Add salt and cream of tartar.
Beat stiff but not dry.
Gradually fold in half the sugar.
Sift remaining flour and sugar together and slowly fold into mixture. Fold in flavoring and water.
Pour into ungreased angel food cake pan. Jar the pan once.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Remove from oven. Invert pan and let stand until cold.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix peanut butter, oleo and sugar well.
Roll into eyeball size balls.
Melt chocolate and wax (while mixing and rolling first mixture).
With a toothpick, pick up the peanut butter balls and roll them in the chocolate, leaving about a dime size circle around the toothpick.
Chill and eat.

title: raisin scones
directions: Grease a baking sheet; set aside.
Preheat oven to 425°.
To make Raisin Scones, in a large bowl stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, cream of tartar and salt.
In another bowl combine margarine, eggs and milk.
Make a well in dry ingredients and add egg mixture; stir until well combined and free of lumps.
Place a 10-inch circle on baking sheet.
With sharp knife, cut dough into 12 wedges.

title: lemon pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order given, but do not use a mixer.

title: scottish scones
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add butter, milk and egg, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened. Stir in raisins. Shape dough into a ball, then pat out on a floured surface into an 8-inch circle. Cut into wedges.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake in a 425° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 8 to 12 scones.

title: dessert bar supreme
directions: Mix cake mix, oatmeal, nuts, one egg and oleo until crumbly. Remove 2 cupfuls and reserve for top.
Press remaining into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat frosting, cream cheese and 2 eggs until creamy. Spread over base in pan.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs over filling. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until firm when slightly shaken.

title: chicken casserole #2
directions: Cook chicken and remove from bone.
Keep 1/4 to 1/2 cup broth. Saute onion in butter until tender.
Cook rice.
Combine chicken, broth, onion and rice with 2 cans soup.
Top with stuffing mix and cook in greased casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: noodles pennsylvania dutch kluski
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large pot of boiling water, cook noodles until tender; drain.
In a large bowl, mix all ingredients together.
Coat a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with nonstick vegetable spray.
Place noodle mixture in baking dish and cover tightly. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until slightly golden around the edges.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: refrigerator cookies(no bake)
directions: Pour into saucepan, milk, oleo and sugar.
Heat until hot but not boiling.
Stir in coconut and vanilla.
Mix in with fork, oats and cocoa.
Mix well and drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet. Put into refrigerator until firm.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake mix by box directions.
Let cake cool.
Then poke holes in cake.
Pour cream of coconut on top, then Eagle Brand, then crushed pineapple, Cool Whip and top with coconut. Refrigerate overnight.
Will stay in refrigerator for days.

title: apricot dessert
directions: Heat pineapple with juice.
Dissolve Jell-O in pineapple.
Mix cream cheese with baby food.
Add Jell-O mixture and Cool Whip. Beat altogether and chill.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil
squash,
onions,
butter and salt until squash is done. (Do not drain.) Stir in cheese until thoroughly blended and then stir in stuffing.
Pour in dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: peaches to make fried pies
directions: Slice peaches with peeling on.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Cook down real low.
Pack hot in jars and seal.
Process jars in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.

title: spanish noodles
directions: Fry meat and onion in butter. Add peppers and celery.
Let this cook for awhile.
Add tomatoes.
Mix boiled noodles and heat. Place in baking dish. Dot with butter.
Add a little more tomato juice. Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake for 1/2 hour in a 350° oven. Serve hot.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook for 1 1/2 hours at 350° in oven.

title: macho potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes and prepare as mashed potatoes with milk and butter.
Add sour cream, bacon, black olives and chives.
Put in 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish and spread cheese over the top.
Broil just to melt cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Place in 10 x 13-inch baking dish. Mix first 3 ingredients and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing packages over casserole.
Boil 2 cups broth, 1 stick butter and vegetable mixes from Stove Top for 5 minutes.
Pour over casserole and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together and form into a ball.
Chill.

title: swiss steak with mushroom gravy
directions: Mix flour with seasoned salt and pepper; coat steak.
Brown quickly.
Mix mushroom soup and milk and pour over steak.
Add onion and mushrooms.
Bake at 350 for 1 hour.
Cut into serving pieces.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil, egg yolks and carrots.
Add water; beat with mixer.
Add remaining ingredients; beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: quick pork tenderloin
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Remove tenderloins from packaging. Place in roasting pan.
Cover with slices of bacon so each tenderloin is covered on all sides.
(Tenderloins can be wrapped in the bacon.)
Keep pan uncovered.
Bake in oven about 30 to 45 minutes, just until the pink is gone; you must check.
Slice into 1/2 to 1-inch slices.
Delicious!
Also great cold.
Serves 4 to 6. (Double for company.)

title: corn bread salad
directions: Prepare corn bread per package instructions; bake and cool. Crumble up corn bread in a bowl.
Add tomatoes, onions, scallions, Miracle Whip and optional ingredients, if desired.
Blend well until moistened and packed.
Dip up with ice cream scoop when ready to serve.

title: good, easy, bread or rolls
directions: Beat all together.
Add 2 c flour gradually.
Put in lightly greased bowl and let rise until double.
If your thumb print remains in dough, it has doubled.
Knead for 5 to 8 minutes and put in greased loaf pan and let rise again.
Also great for dinner rolls or cinnamon rolls.
Bake at 350°.
Yield 1 loaf.

title: winter squash bisque
directions: Halve squash and remove seeds.
Place squash halves, cut side down, on a baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Turn cut sides up.
Bake, covered, 20 to 25 minutes or until squash is tender.

title: apple cake cobbler
directions: In a 9 x 13 inch baking dish, spread apple pie filling, sprinkle cinnamon over top.
Spread dry cake mix over first layer. Combine brown sugar and nuts and spread over second layer.
Layer butter patties over entire top of cake.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Top with vanilla ice cream to serve if desired.
Yield: 15 servings.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown ground beef and season to taste.
Add tomato sauce and 1 can of water.
Simmer about 10 to 15 minutes. Add all ingredients except corn chips.
Stir well, then crunch up corn chips and stir into mixture. Pour into casserole dish and sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° about 25 to 30 minutes.
Add raisins if you like.

title: gail's blintz casserole
directions: Butter bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dip blintzes in melted butter.
Mix sugar, vanilla, sour cream, eggs and orange juice in blender.
Pour over blintzes.
Sprinkle cinnamon over blintzes. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Can use other flavor blintzes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine oil, molasses, sugar, egg and vanilla and mix well. Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Spoon batter in greased muffin tins, filling each two-thirds full.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: thanksgiving cranberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine dry cake mix, cinnamon and nutmeg in bowl.
Cut in butter with pastry blender or two knives until crumbly.
Stir in nuts; set aside.

title: cheese and garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix ingredients until soft dough forms. If dough is too sticky, gradually mix in enough baking mix (up to 2 tablespoons) to make dough easy to handle.
Turn onto surface dusted with baking mix.
Roll in baking mix to coat.
Shape into ball and knead gently 10 times.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with 2-inch cutter dipped in baking mix.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine syrup, sugar and butter in pan and heat to boiling. Beat the eggs and salt until light.
Gradually pour hot syrup over eggs; beat constantly.
Add vanilla and blend.
Pour in pie shell and sprinkle pecan meats over top and bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix
well
pretzels, 1 tablespoon of sugar and softened margarine.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with mixture.
Bake at 400° for about 8 minutes.
Let cool.
Beat cream cheese, 1/2 cup of sugar and
Cool
Whip
together.
Spread on cooled crust.
Mix boiling water and jello until dissolved.
Add strawberries and juice. Refrigerate jello until slightly thickened.
Pour over mixture. Refrigerate until completely thickened.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Boil the sugar, oil and vinegar.
Pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: pizza lasagna
directions: Brown beef and sausage together, then drain.
Add mushrooms, onion and spaghetti sauce.
Let simmer.
Cook lasagna noodles. Combine cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese and eggs, then set aside.

title: pasta primavera with shrimp
directions: While pasta water comes to a boil, get all ingredients ready to cook before adding the pasta to the boiling water.

title: red refrigerator pudding
directions: Mix together and add 1 can crushed pineapple and 1 cup nuts. Mix and set aside.
Layer in Pyrex dish graham crackers, sugar/pineapple mix and make 3 layers.
Pour on red jello and refrigerator.

title: chile-cheese rice(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Saut onion in butter in a large saucepan until tender.
Remove from heat; stir in next 7 ingredients.
Spoon half of rice mixture into a lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with half of cheese. Top with remaining rice mixture.
Bake at 375°, uncovered, 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese; bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: vanilla fudge
directions: In a heavy saucepan, mix and bring to a boil sugar and whipping cream, stirring constantly.

Add cream of tartar. Continue to boil until mixture reaches soft boil stage, 234° to 240° on candy thermometer or when a small amount of mixture dropped from a spoon into ice water forms a ball which does not disintegrate but flattens out when picked up with your fingers. When candy has reached that stage, remove from heat and mix until creamy.
Add vanilla and nuts, if desired.
Cover pan with a damp cloth and let sit 1/2 hour.
Press into a shallow pan that has been lined with waxed paper.
When cooked, cut into squares. Makes 1 pound.

title: quick chocolate chip cookie pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pierce pie crust (frozen) with fork. Bake in preheated oven for 10 minutes, until slightly browned. Mix cookie mix as directed.
Add self rising flour.
Pour into pie crust.
bake at 350° until center rises.
Check for doneness with toothpick (approximately 35 minutes).

title: texas hash
directions: Fry onions and pepper in Crisco until onions turn yellow. Mix all ingredients together.
Place in oiled baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar, oleo, eggs, vinegar, and vanilla well.
Mix in coconut.
Then pour in unbaked pie shell and bake 40 or 50 minutes at 350 or until brown.

title: elaine's banana cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350°F until done, about 30 minutes.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain all but 3 tablespoons grease.
Saute vegetables in remaining grease.
Set aside.

title: missouri cookies
directions: Place first four ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook at a rolling boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, salt and Quaker oats.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper immediately.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut tops off peppers.
Remove seeds and membrane.
Brown meat and onion.
Add tomatoes, rice, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer until rice is tender, 5 minutes.
Add cheese.
Stuff peppers;
cover with tops.
Stand upright in baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together and put in oblong pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: melt-in-your-mouth chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in lightly greased casserole dish.
Mix soup and broth well.
Pour over chicken.
In a separate bowl, mix other ingredients to form batter.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: holly cookies
directions: Put vanilla, oleo, marshmallows and food coloring in top of double boiler and melt.
Remove from heat and stir in corn flakes with metal spoon.
Drop mixture onto wax paper.
Use metal knife to push off spoon to form holly.
Trim with cinnamon hearts.

title: low-fat chicken breast
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spray pan with Pam.
Stir mustard, yogurt and vinegar together.
In second dish, combine potato granules and Parmesan cheese.
Dip chicken first in mustard, then in potato mixture, coating both sides well.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes, until coating is light brown.
Makes 4 servings, 6 grams of fat per serving.

title: party pizza
directions: Unroll dough.
Pat dough onto bottom of 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Overlap and press rolls to fit.
Set aside.
Combine sausage and mustard.
Lightly brown and drain.
Spoon evenly over dough in pan.
Sprinkle with broccoli, pepper, onion and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes until crust is golden.
May be cooked ahead of time and reheated at serving time.
Store in airtight container until heated.
This is quick and easy for any party or gathering.

title: punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and water; add rest of ingredients.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: In bowl, mix first 6 ingredients and set aside.
In large bowl beat oleo and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Stir in zucchini and vanilla.
Alternately add dry ingredients and milk. Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° in Bundt or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Test with toothpick.

title: caramel orange fondue
directions: Melt caramels with orange juice in covered double boiler or in saucepan over low heat.
Stir occasionally until sauce is smooth. Add orange rind.
Pour into fondue pot; keep warm while serving. Dip cake into caramel sauce; roll in almonds.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: barbecued beef and pork
directions: Mix together, except for pickling spice.
Cook for 30 minutes. Add the pickling spice in a bag.

title: hearty rice casserole
directions: Saute bell pepper, celery and onion in oil until clear and tender.
Add broth and rice; stir and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in mushroom soup.
Pour into casserole dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Decorate with pimento strips.
Cover and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: caramel apple streusel
directions: Arrange apples in microwavable baking dish.
Stir together caramel topping, water and lemon juice.
Pour over apples.
In a small bowl combine flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle evenly over apples.
Microwave on High for 5 to 7 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water and add frozen juice. Stir until melted; then add pineapple with juice and oranges, drained.
Chill until firm.

title: eye of round roast(the low-fat way)
directions: Trim all fat from roast.
Place in roaster.
Add potatoes, carrots, onions and celery or your choices.
Pour tomatoes and water over all.
Season with pepper, celery seed, garlic and bouillon.
Cover.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours until done.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add mushroom soup.
Layer beef and onion in baking dish.
Top with Tater Tots and cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until done.

title: lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown ground chuck in skillet with meat tenderizer, garlic salt and pepper; drain off grease.
Add Ragu sauce and tomato paste; simmer 1 hour. Boil lasagna with 1 teaspoon salt for 15 minutes.
Mix cottage cheese with 2 eggs.

In a large casserole dish, spread 2 to 3 tablespoons meat sauce. Layer noodles, meat sauce and cottage cheese mixture 2 to 3 times. Top with Mozzarella and sprinkle Parmesan on last. Bake about 1 hour.
Allow to cool 10 minutes before cutting.

title: curried fruit
directions: Combine butter or margarine, sugar and curry powder.
Bring to a boil.
Drain the fruit.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat in large skillet; drain off fat.
Add garlic and salt; simmer 5 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and tomato paste.
Cook, stirring occasionally, 10 to 15 minutes.
Boil lasagna for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Combine egg, Ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese, parsley and pepper.
Blend well.
In a greased lasagna pan arrange a layer of lasagna.
Spread with Ricotta mixture, meat sauce and Mozzarella.
Repeat, topping with sauce and Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and top with some of remaining stuffing. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: the best potato salad
directions: Boil red potatoes whole, test for doneness with sharp-pointed knife.
Cool, dice, leaving about 1/2 of the peelings on.
Salt to taste.
Mix and add all other ingredients.
If too dry, add more sour cream or salad dressing.
Sprinkle with paprika. Refrigerate.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: taco pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Line pan with crescent rolls.
Line crust with 1 cup Fritos and ground beef mixture.
Spread on sour cream.
Sprinkle with cheese and top with 1 cup Fritos.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: very berry pie
directions: Prepare pudding mix as directed (over stove).
Remove from heat and add cream cheese.
Beat with electric beater until smooth.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour in crust.
Refrigerate for 3 hours or overnight.
Decorate with fresh strawberries or blueberries. Serve with whipped cream.

title: 5 hour beef stew
directions: Mix together in ovenproof kettle.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours. Serve with hot bread or cornbread.

title: fried eggplant with pork hash
directions: Thinly slice the eggplants;
soak for a few minutes and dry with paper towel.
Fry in oil until brown and tender; set aside. Brown the
pork hash or ground chicken in skillet; add chicken broth to
cover
hash.
Add the remaining ingredients; simmer 10 to	15
minutes.
Thicken with cornstarch.	Layer as follows: pork
hash	mixture,
fried
eggplant, thinly sliced fried eggs and green onion.

title: hershey pie
directions: Melt Hershey bar in a 400° oven.
Put marshmallows and Cool Whip into bowl.
Add Hershey bar and whip with a wooden spoon. Put into crust and refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: russian chicken
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Place chicken in baking dish. Pour mixture over chicken.
Cover.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350° or until chicken is done.
Serve with rice.

title: pineapple, cheese and nut salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water; let cool.
Whip Dream Whip and add cream cheese, pineapple, cooled jello and nuts.
Pour into square or oblong pan and refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Pound chicken breasts between sheets of wax paper to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut cream cheese into cubes.
Place 1 cube in each piece of chicken and roll up, securing with bacon slices and toothpick.
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli; drain and save liquid.
Saute onions in margarine (1 tablespoon).
Mix flour with milk in shaker and shake well.
Stir while cooking over medium heat until sauce thickens. Add cheese and stir until it melts.
Add rest of ingredients: liquid, milk, salt, pepper and broccoli.
Cook until heated through.
This recipe may be doubled or tripled.
Serves 6.

title: chicken breasts in sour cream
directions: Arrange chicken in shallow baking pan; don't overlap.
Cover with mushrooms.
Combine soup, wine and sour cream; stir until blended.
Pour over chicken, completely covering and dust with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with noodles or baked potatoes.

title: lazy man's peach pie
directions: Melt oleo.
Make a batter of sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour batter over margarine.
Then add fruit and juices. Bake at 350° until dough is brown and cooked through fruit, 50 to 60 minutes.

title: spinach fruit salad
directions: Clean spinach and tear into bite-size pieces, slice fruits and add to salad.
Top with dressing and toss, or serve on the side.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift 2 1/2 cups flour, baking powder, salt and 1/2 cup sugar. Add next 3 ingredients and mix only until dry ingredients are dampened.
Mix berries with 2 tablespoons flour.
Fold in berries. Fill greased muffin tins 2/3's full.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with lots of butter.
Makes 16 to 24 muffins.

title: wheat germ fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except apples and lettuce.
Mix well. Arrange apple slices in fan shape on lettuce leaves.
Top with cheese mixture.
Makes 4 servings.
tags: Kretschmer wheat germ with brown sugar

title: make a dream pie
directions: With an electric mixer, mix together the whipped topping, 1 cup milk and vanilla flavoring; beat at high speed for 6 minutes, or until topping thickens and forms peaks.
Add remaining milk and the pie filing; blend on low until mixed well, then beat on high for 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Spoon into pie shell and chill at least 4 hours.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add sugar and continue beating until stiff.
Add salt and vanilla, mix well.
Add pecans and choice of other ingredients.

title: graham cracker bars
directions: Boil sugar, oil and nuts until sugar is dissolved.
Put graham crackers on cookie sheet.
Break in half.
Pour mixture over crackers, spreading evenly and bake 8 minutes at 350°.

title: roberta's baked beans
directions: Boil beans 2 hours using plenty of water.
Drain most all water.
Add rest ingredients.
Bake at 325° for at least 4 hours or use crock-pot.

title: ham with peach glaze
directions: Place ham on a rack in roasting pan.
Score the surface with shallow diagonal cuts, making diamond shapes; insert whole cloves into diamonds.
Secure pineapple slices and cherries on ham with toothpicks.
In a small bowl, combine the brown sugar, peach nectar, vinegar, ground cloves.
Spoon half of glaze over ham.

title: marinated asparagus salad
directions: In saucepan, dissolve sugar in vinegar.
Add oil and heat until hot.
Add peppers and onions; heat for a few minutes.

title: tuna dressing
directions: Combine and pour all ingredients into an 8 x 8 x 1-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 1.

title: orange-almond salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a jar; shake and then chill for about 1 hour.
Toss dressing over greens and top with slivered almonds.

title: praline cookies
directions: Cream shortening with sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour and soda, mixing well.
Add oatmeal, mixing well. Form into two long rolls and chill for at least 1 hour.
Slice into 1/4-inch slices and bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: bananas foster ala microwave
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir together
brown
sugar and rum.
Add butter.
Cover.
Microwave at High setting
4 or 5 minutes.
Stir after 2 minutes until sugar
is
dissolved. Cut bananas
lengthwise, then crosswise so there are 8 pieces. Add to syrup,
stirring
to
cover
each
piece.
Top
banana mixture with crumbled cookies.
Microwave at High setting 1 to 2 minutes until hot.	Serve over vanilla ice cream.
Serves 4.

title: barbara's frozen salad
directions: Blend mayonnaise and cream cheese.
Add fruit, nuts and marshmallows.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into mold and freeze. Take out about 10 minutes before serving.

title: tropical chicken
directions: Combine soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce, honey, ginger, mustard, vegetable oil and pineapple.
Brush mixture onto chicken breasts and grill until done, basting breasts as often as needed.

title: homemade b.b.q.  sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in a heavy boiler. Simmer for about 30 minutes. Put into squeeze bottles. Makes about 60 oz.

title: corn dogs
directions: In large bowl, mix corn meal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in egg, milk and Crisco.
Dip hot dogs in batter and fry in deep fryer until golden brown.

title: hot spinach dip(holiday)
directions: In ovenproof bowl, blend all ingredients except 1/2 cup of Mozzarella cheese until smooth.
Then top with remaining cheese. In preheated 350° oven, cook 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pina colada slush
directions: Mix all together and freeze.
Serve with sweet or sour soda.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Bake cake per instructions and bake on cookie sheet.
Mix cream cheese with 1/2 cup milk until creamy.
Add pudding and an additional 1 1/2 cups milk.
Mix. Add drained pineapple.
Spread over cooled cake.
Frost with Cool Whip.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cover bottom of pan with oil.
Saute the onion until tender. Add potatoes; pour water to cover and cook.
Add clam juice, baby clams, minced clams and chopped clams.
When potatoes are cooked, add tomato soup; stir and let simmer.
Do not boil.
This makes a big quantity!

title: cheese and grits
directions: Cook grits and cheese in double boiler.
Add a dash of Worcestershire sauce, butter, mustard, flour and egg yolks until thickened, then add egg whites, beaten.
Add to grits.
Bake for about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and keep cool.
When ready to serve, scoop several scoops or 1/2 carton orange sherbet into punch bowl after punch has been poured into bowl.

title: hamburger vegetable casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Mix with potatoes and soup.
Add 1 can of water.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mysterious black olive dip(serves 8)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°. Serve with crackers.

title: baked lime chicken
directions: In medium saucepan combine all ingredients except chicken, bring to a boil.
Place chicken in marinade and simmer 20 minutes. Remove from heat and let stand several hours in refrigerator. Grill chicken, turning and basting frequently.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Line bottom of casserole with large marshmallows.
Peel and cook the potatoes until done; mash.
Add the vanilla and pour over the marshmallows.
Melt margarine; add the nuts and brown sugar and pour on top of the potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cold bean salad
directions: Drain all beans.
In large bowl, add beans to bell pepper, onion and celery.
Blend together vinegar, sugar and salad oil. Pour over bean mixture.
Mix all well.
Place in refrigerator for 12 hours before serving.
Serves 10.

title: ranch layered salad
directions: In 3-quart or 4-quart bowl, layer salad greens, mushrooms, tomatoes, carrots and peas.
Add green onions.
Spoon dressing over salad mixture spreading to cover top.
Cover; refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight before serving.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Boil eggs and chicken.
Debone chicken and layer in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream of chicken soup and vegetables over low heat.
Pour over chicken.
Slice eggs and lay over the top.
Take each canned biscuit and mash it flat, then slice into strips and lay on top. Bake at 325° until biscuits are done.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Melt the margarine in 2-quart dish.
Mix together in the dish the sugar, flour, baking powder and milk. Add the rhubarb. Sprinkle with the sugar.
Don't mix. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: northern chinese pork
directions: Debone pork, cube and marinate in soy sauce, sherry and ginger.
Meanwhile, peel and chop onion and celery and grate carrots into coarse pieces.

title: sheath cake
directions: Bring oleo, cocoa, oil and water to a boil.
Pour the boiling mixture over the remaining ingredients.
Beat all at once, and bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: fruited ambrosia
directions: In large bowl, combine Eagle Brand, sour cream and lime juice; mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill 3 hours or longer to blend flavors.
Serve chilled.

title: sausage, chicken and rice dish
directions: Brown and cube chicken.
Brown and cut up sausage.
Brown 1 onion.
Add few pieces of garlic, red pepper, green pepper, cayenne pepper and bouillon (already dissolved in water).
Add this to mixture.
Add rice.
Mix everything together.
Cook until water is absorbed approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Mix occasionally.
Serve hot.

title: corn pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well, adding corn last.
Pour into a greased baking dish and dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into ice cream freezer and freeze.

title: texas goulash
directions: Saute ground round, green beans, corn, tomatoes, green peppers, chopped celery and onion.
Cut okra and add to mixture. Add 1/2 cup of tomato ketchup, salt, pepper and paprika to taste. Put all ingredients into baking pan.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top of the ingredients.
Put in oven at 300° until dish is bubbling.

title: apple muffins (diabetic)
directions: Stir Sweet One, sugar and oil.
Add egg white.
Stir well, add flour, salt, soda, vanilla and apples, applesauce and cinnamon. Bake at 375°.

title: jenna's favorite homemade graham crackers
directions: Place whole wheat flour in bowl.
Cut in butter until mixture is the consistency of coarse oatmeal.
Add sugar, baking soda, cream of tartar, egg and enough hot water to make a dough that can be rolled like pastry.
Roll out dough to 1/8 to 1/4-inch consistency on floured board (use unbleached white flour for rolling).
Cut into 3-inch squares.
Place on ungreased baking sheet in a 350° preheated oven and bake for 15 to 20 minutes, or until done.
Cool on rack.
Yields about 2 dozen crackers.
Great served while warm.

title: preacher's cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage in small pieces.
Add all ingredients and cook in a large skillet for 12 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain.
Saute onion and butter. Add to drained broccoli.
Cook rice until medium tender; add to broccoli mix.
Pour soup in and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: favas
directions: Soak favas overnight.
Add salt and boil until done (3 hours). In a separate pan, slice onions into butter and cook until done. Add sauce and 1 can of water.
Add spices as desired.
Combine both pans and cook together for 1 hour.

title: green bean salad
directions: Mix all liquids, sugar, salt and pepper. Let set 1 hour, stirring occasionally to dissolve sugar. Add all other ingredients and mix well. Cover and store in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: company cheese cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix cracker crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar and the 3 tablespoons melted butter.
Press in bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake 10 minutes and cool.
Heat oven to 300°. Beat cream cheese in large mixer bowl; add the cup sugar gradually, beating until fluffy.
Add lemon peel and vanilla. Beat in 1 egg at a time.
Pour into pan.
Bake until center is firm about one hour.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix first three ingredients and put in bottom of 9x13 pan, bake at 375 for 10 minutes.
Cool and set aside.
Combine next two ingredients, mix well, fold in cool whip, then spread on pretzel layer.
Chill.
Mix jello and water until dissolved.
Add frozen strawberries.
When it starts to gel, pour over cream cheese mixture.
Chill a couple of hours then serve.

title: microwave oniony cream sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 1-quart glass bowl.
Cover. Microwave at power level Low and Defrost for 6 1/2 to 8 minutes, or until warm.
Beat mixture to blend well.
Microwave, uncovered, at power level High for 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes, or until hot, stirring once.
Makes about 1 3/4 cups.

title: liptauer cheese spread
directions: Allow cream cheese and butter to reach room temperature. Blend all ingredients in food processor and serve with mini rye breads.

title: cheese ball
directions: Leave cheese out until soft at room temperature.
Mix cheeses well.
Add onion, garlic and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix with cheese mixture thoroughly.
Serve with crackers.

title: cheese appetizers
directions: Mix butter, cheese, Tabasco, Worcestershire and onion powder. Beat until light and fluffy.
Spread mixture on each bread slice. Stack 4 high and trim crusts.
Sprinkle top slice with dill weed and cayenne pepper.
Cut into fourths.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: roman delight quiche
directions: Beat 4 eggs and Parmesan cheese together.
Smooth 1 package rolls on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Layer 1/2 of salami, ham and Provolone.
Spread 1/2 of peppers over top.
Pour 1/2 of egg/cheese mixture over top, tilting pan to spread.
Repeat process (omitting layer of rolls).
Top with remaining package of rolls and brush with reserved beaten egg.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes covered with foil (tent foil to prevent sticking) 10 to 15 minutes uncovered.
Cool and cut into desired shapes and sizes.
May be served hot or cold.
Can be reheated; refrigerates well.
Freezes well.

title: raisin-apple dressing
directions: Soak bread in milk. Stir in eggs.
Add apples and raisins. Pour into baking dish.
Pour some meat juice over top and bake. Baste as needed.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: marshmallow fudge cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Blend in melted chocolate. Sift flour and dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternately with liquid and vanilla.
Pour into 2 greased and floured pans and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Frost with Marshmallow Frosting (Seven Minute Frosting with marshmallows added).

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugar and eggs; cream well.
Add flour and vanilla.
Beat well.
Fold in potato chips and nuts.
Make into balls and flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar; let stand.
Mix dry ingredients with apples.
Add eggs, oil and vanilla.
Mix all and put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: fried apple pies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, apples, and 3 tsp. cinnamon sugar in a large skillet.
Fry on low heat, covered, until apples are tender. Roll biscuits out about 1/2 inch thick.
Place a tsp. of apples in the center.
Fold over, then use fork and press firmly around the edges.
Place in skillet of melted butter (or margarine) and sprinkle with cinnamon sugar on both sides.
Fry until golden brown.

title: lemon pie
directions: Boil water, sugar and flour for 15 minutes, then add egg yolks, butter, salt and lemons.
Use egg whites for meringue. This recipe makes 2 pies (use 1/2 recipe for one pie).

title: basic white bread
directions: Place shortening, sugar and salt in mixing bowl.
Add hot milk and stir to soften shortening.
Let cool.
Beat in eggs.
Soften yeast in the warm water; add to shortening mixture.
Add 4 cups of flour.
Beat smooth.
Add enough of rest of flour to make soft dough; knead 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl.
Turn over once so top of dough is greased.
Cover with cloth and let rise until double (approximately 1 1/4 hours).
Punch down and let rest 10 minutes.
Shape into loaves and place into greased pans.
Let rise again (about 1 hour).
Bake at 400° for 25 or 30 minutes. Remove from pans immediately and let cool.

title: tea time sandwiches
directions: Blend cream cheese softened with strawberry preserves; stir in chopped pecans.
Spread on date nut bread; garnish with pecan halves.

title: pinto beans and rice casserole
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart dish, combine the beans, picante sauce, rice, beef and half the cheese.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 20 to 25 minutes until heated through.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Serve with tortilla chips if desired.

title: beef roast
directions: Dissolve the sugar and flour in the tomato juice.
Put meat and vegetables in casserole or covered baking dish.
Pour tomatoes, flour and sugar over meat and cook covered for 5 hours at 250°.

title: devue's deep fried oysters
directions: Drain oysters; reserve liquid.
Mix all other ingredients to oyster liquid.
Dip oysters in the batter.
Put in deep fat fryer. Cook until golden brown.
Makes 18 puffs.
You can substitute mushrooms for the oysters and they are great also.

title: cheese ball
directions: Shape into ball.
Chill overnight.
Roll in 1 or 2 cups finely chopped pecans.

title: macaroni salad(from day old macaroni)
directions: Mix macaroni and vegetables in a bowl.
Stir in Miracle Whip.

title: italian sausage and potato casserole
directions: Put above ingredients into a large casserole and toss together.
Arrange sausage on top of potatoes and cover all with foil.
Bake at 375° about 45 minutes or till potatoes are tender. Uncover and bake 15 - 20 minutes more.
Delicious!

title: arroz con cerdo
directions: Saute bacon until almost crisp in large frying pan. Roll each slice while still warm around tines of fork to make bacon curls. Drain on paper towel and set aside. Pour all drippings into a cup. Brown pork slowly, a little at a time, in the same pan. Return 2 tablespoons of bacon drippings to pan. Add onion and garlic and saute until soft. Push to 1 side. Add rice and saute, stirring constantly, until golden. Stir in instant chicken broth, saffron and water. Heat to boiling and pour into a 12-cup baking dish. Top with browned pork and cover. Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour or until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender. Fluff up with a fork. Stand bacon curls in a ring in center. Spoon cooked peas around edge. Makes 8 servings.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Cut in oleo and add remaining ingredients.
Knead on floured board.
Form into round ball. Flatten on greased pan 1 1/2 inches thick.
Cut across with knife. Baste top with 1 egg and 1 teaspoon water, mixed.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: nut balls
directions: Put syrup, vanilla and salt into bowl; mix together.
Add powdered milk and chopped nuts.
Stir with knife until well blended.
