Pat into ball; place on board sprinkled lightly with sugar.
Knead until creamy.
Let stand until firm enough to shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Yields 1/2 pound.

title: stir-fry brown rice and vegetables
directions: The day or morning before serving, cook rice according to package directions, adding chicken bouillon granules to water. Cool rice completely in refrigerator.

title: pasta aglio-olie e' pomidori freschi(pasta with garlic and oil with fresh tomatoes)
directions: In a bowl, mash garlic with salt.
Add mint leaves and mash. Add olive oil.
In another bowl, chop tomatoes.
Add garlic and oil ingredients.
Do not cook.
Cook spaghetti al dente.
Drain pasta; reserve 1/2 cup pasta water and add to tomatoes, and toss with pasta.
Serve with cheese.
This is a very old family favorite.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: In a pan, heat the brown sugar, milk and butter.
Stir so it won't stick.
Let boil 2 minutes and pour over hot cake in pan.

title: pomegranate jelly(mcp cooked jelly recipe)
directions: Mom always told me to add a dash of salt to any recipe requiring a quantity of sugar.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix until well blended. Pour into prepared pan. Bake about 55 minutes.
Heat oven to 350° and grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.

title: crab dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Soften cream cheese.
Add sour cream and beat until smooth.
Add Worcestershire sauce, mayo and garlic salt.
Mix in crab meat.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into prepared crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set. Top with cherry pie filling before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: chicken cabbage salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour on dressing and mix well.

title: weight watcher apple-bran muffins
directions: Mix all but applesauce, then add applesauce and mix well. Spoon into 24 "Pam" sprayed muffin tins.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°. Makes 24.

title: sombreros
directions: Blend cheese and butter.
Add flour and seasonings.
Blend well.
Shape into small balls around olives.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: flat bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients to make a moist, not sticky, dough. Pinch off a tablespoon (approximately) at a time and press into 5-inch patty, like a tortilla.
Fry patties in heavy skillet, well coated with oil, until golden brown.
Serve hot.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen 5-inch loaves.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Mix all
together.
Split buns and butter.
Fill.
Wrap in foil.
Put in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: roast turkey with chestnut stuffing
directions: First make the stuffing:
Put the bacon in a nonstick saute pan and cook over low heat until the fat is released.
Add the chestnuts and cook over medium heat for 10 minutes, or until the bacon is crisp.
Add the bread crumbs.
Transfer to a bowl and let cool.
Add the egg, watercress, and salt and pepper; mix well. Preheat oven to 350°.
Spoon the cold stuffing into the neck end of the bird, pull the skin over and secure with a skewer.
Twist the wing tips up and over; tie wings and legs with string.
Spread the butter over the bird, sprinkle with salt and pepper, then place, breast side up, on a rack in a roasting pan.
If using a meat thermometer, push it into the thickest part of a thigh, away from the bone.
Roast for 3 to 3 1/2 hours, until juices run clear.
If using a thermometer, the temperature should read 185°.
If the bird browns before it is cooked, cover with foil and continue roasting. Let the bird stand, wrapped in foil, while you make the gravy.

title: best banana pudding
directions: Make pudding by box directions except use only 3 cups of milk plus the Eagle Brand milk.
Mix lemon juice and bananas together. Stir Cool Whip into pudding mixture.
Then layer in serving dish as follows:
wafers, bananas, then pudding.
Extra delicious if you top with a pint of fresh whipped cream.
Chill before serving.

title: persimmon marmalade
directions: Wash, cut up and press persimmons through sieve.
Measure pulp.
To each cup of pulp, add one cup sugar and cook slowly 20 minutes, stirring constantly.
(Do not boil as jam will become bitter.)
Pour in sterilized jelly jars to within 1/4-inch of top. Put on scalded caps and screw bands firmly tight.
Process 10 minutes in boiling water bath.
Each cup of pulp makes about 1/2 pint jam.

title: garden fresh salad
directions: Mix together in a sealed container.
Let marinate overnight. Enjoy.

title: chopped chicken livers
directions: Score livers with a sharp knife; wash, drain and sprinkle with salt.
Broil chicken livers 3 to 5 minutes or until cooked. Grind livers finely with onion and hard-cooked eggs.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Add enough chicken fat to make mixture that is smooth and has the consistency of mashed potatoes.
Serve on lettuce with wedges of tomato.
Makes 4 appetizer servings.
Also delicious spread on crackers.

title: chocolate macaroons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook milk and chocolate over low heat until thick. Add coconut, nuts, coffee (or rum) and vanilla. Drop on greased cookie sheets and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: roast in the coals(it won't be salty - it won't be dry!)
directions: Prepare fire so you have a good bed of hot embers.
You should have a large, wide fire so that coals can be raked up as needed.

title: coated cereal snack
directions: In a large bowl, mix all cereals, pretzels and nuts.
Melt 2 squares of white almond bark in the microwave.
Put bark in a large pan; heat on High for 1 minute and 20 seconds.
Pour cereal mixture into melted bark.
Stir with spoon until well coated. Pour mixture on aluminum foil and cool.
Break apart and store in tin or airtight container.
If you want to drop on foil like a cookie, melt 4 to 6 squares of bark for same amount of ingredients.

title: corn spoon bread
directions: Combine all in 11 x 7-inch dish.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°. Double for large cake.

title: easy double chocolate chip brownies
directions: Melt 1 cup morsels and butter in large, heavy saucepan over low heat; stir until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs; stir well. Add flour, sugar, baking soda and vanilla; stir well.
Stir in remaining 1 cup morsels and nuts.
Spread into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 18 to 22 minutes until wooden pick inserted in center comes out still slightly sticky.
Cool completely.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: mock mayonnaise
directions: Boil sugar, flour and water for 1 minute.
In blender put egg yolks, vinegar, lemon juice, salt, mustard and pepper.
Blend. Slowly add hot mixture and blend well, then slowly add oil and blend until smooth.
Store in refrigerator.

title: fresh fruit dip(very easy and really good!)
directions: Boil wings in water to remove fat.
Fry wings in margarine until brown.
Put in baking pan.
Combine all ingredients together in a bowl.
Mix together and pour mixture over wings.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours, turning every 15 minutes or so.
Done when sticky.

title: stroganoff for the incredibly lazy
directions: Brown meat, onion and seasoning.
Add cream of mushroom soup. Stir in milk until thick gravy consistency.
When heated through add sour cream and heat through again.
Serve over hot buttered noodles.
May be made in crock-pot.
Brown meat and combine all ingredients in crock-pot and cook on low about 4 hours.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown and drain beef, stir in beans, tomato sauce, chili powder and garlic salt and heat to boiling.
Place chips in a greased casserole dish.
Top with beef mix.
Spread sour cream over all.
Sprinkle onions over, then chopped tomato.
Spread cheese on top and bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with salad.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Make a skillet of cornbread (do not make thick).
Boil hen in 1 1/2 quarts water.
Crumble corn bread and slices of bread.
Add vegetables that have been simmered for about 5 minutes in 1/2 cup of broth.
Make sure everything is cool that goes into the bread crumbs.
(If hot water is used, bread will gum together.)
Add seasonings, chopped eggs, beaten raw eggs and meat, if desired. Pour broth over mixture, stirring lightly so as not to mash up crumbs.
Bake in a 400° oven until brown.
Stir one time while baking.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place deboned chicken in a large casserole dish.
Mix water and soup; then pour over chicken.
Salt lightly.
Mix melted margarine, buttermilk and flour; pour over layer of soup.
Pour 2 cups of broth over this and bake at 350° until crust rises and browns (approximately 45 minutes).

title: baby peas and water chestnuts casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion, peppers and celery.
Saute over medium heat until soft.
Remove from heat.
Add peas and water chestnuts.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix in order given.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Divide batter between two well-greased 8 x 4-inch loaf pans.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes in 350° oven or until bread tests done with toothpick.
Turn out onto rack to cool.

title: four cheese ball
directions: Cream Bleu and cream cheeses together.
Shred Jack and Cheddar. Add with 1 ounce of dry white wine and a few drops of sauce (or Tabasco sauce if you like it; I don't).
Blend well.
Make into ball and roll in chopped nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: plum cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar and spices; mix well.
Add oil, eggs and plums.
Mix on high speed 3 to 4 minutes.
Add 1 cup chopped nuts. Pour into well-greased Bundt pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan for 20 minutes and then finish cooling on rack.
Wrap in foil to keep for 1 week.
Freezes well.

title: puppy chow for people
directions: Melt butter on stove top or in microwave.
Add chocolate chips and stir.
Heat until melted.
Add peanut butter and stir well. Add cereal and gently stir to coat.
Pour mixture into a large Ziploc bag with powdered sugar.
Shake to coat in bite size pieces.

title: pear bread
directions: Cream the butter gradually, then beat in sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to egg mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in pears and vanilla.
Pour into buttered 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken squares
directions: Cook and shred chicken.
Melt together butter and cream cheese; add chicken.
Put mixture in crescent rolls; pinch together sides.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 20 minutes.
Heat cheese soup; pour over squares when done cooking.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll one quarter apple per biscuit.
Place in 13 x 9 inch baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Bring to a boil and pour over apple dumplings.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
You may also use strawberries or peaches.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a
greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: chinese egg rolls
directions: Put celery and cabbage in 1/2 cup water.
Bring to a boil. Drain thoroughly.
Heat oil in a large skillet.
Add shrimp and meat.
Cook 2 or 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add remaining ingredients and continue cooking and stirring until delicately browned.
Cool.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Make a glaze by adding sugar, strawberry flavoring and food color to boiling water in a saucepan.
Add dissolved cornstarch and stir over medium heat until thickened.
Remove and set aside.
Add cool prepared Pastry Cream to the bottom of the pie shell.
Pour in half pint of strawberries.
Cover with half of the glaze and add remaining strawberries, covering with glaze.
Decorate the edges with whipped cream.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Chill and serve.

title: yummy chicken casserole
directions: Cut up chicken pieces and place in bottom of casserole dish. Mix soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Top with crackers and margarine.
(Mix with crushed crackers and sprinkle on top.)
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: Place first five ingredients into a medium bowl.
Add mayonnaise.
Refrigerate at least one hour or overnight.

title: berry wine sauce
directions: In a saucepan, melt sugar in berries over low heat.
Mix cornstarch in wine.
Pour into heated berries/sugar mixture.
Stir carefully (try not to crush berries) until mixture clears (shortly after it comes to a boil).
If it seems too thick, add wine or water, then bring back to a boil until desired consistency.

title: onion casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch buttered casserole, alternate layers of thinly sliced onions, crushed potato chips and grated cheese.
Mix milk with soups and pour over layers.
Sprinkle cayenne pepper over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
This is good with barbecue pork or ham.

title: snowdrift
directions: Mix flour, pecans and melted butter together.
Spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip together.
Spread on top of flour layer.
Mix pudding, use only 4 cups milk.
Spread on top of cream cheese layer.
Spread Cool Whip on top of pudding. Grate chocolate bar on top.

title: whipped turnip casserole
directions: Cook turnips and mash.
Add butter, sugar, salt and pepper; beat with mixer.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well until soft and fluffy.
Stir in breadcrumbs and lemon juice.
Pour into casserole.
If preparing ahead, cool and chill.
Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven for 50 minutes until top is slightly brown.

title: chinese new year chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with garlic salt; roll in cornstarch.
Dip in eggs.
Cook in a small amount of oil in a frying pan until brown; place in a shallow casserole.
Mix monosodium glutamate, sugar, stock, vinegar, salt, soy sauce and catsup; pour over chicken. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Crush the package of Oreos and place half in the bottom of an 11 x 17-inch pan.
Save the rest of the crushed cookies for the top.
Use a mixer to blend Cool Whip, cream cheese, sugar and margarine.

In a bowl, combine milk, pudding and vanilla extract. Beat this mixture until it is the consistency of pudding. Combine both mixtures and pour over the layer of crushed cookies. Sprinkle the remaining cookies on the top.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a large spoon.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts last.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican pizza dip
directions: Mix cream cheese spread and 1 cup of the shredded cheese. Spread onto bottom of 9 inch pie plate.
Top with salsa and remaining 1/2 cup shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until dip is heated through and cheese is melted.
Sprinkle with desired toppings.
Serve as a hot dip with crackers or chips.

title: caramel
directions: Cook sugar, Karo and butter until thick and clear.
Very slowly, add cream, stirring constantly; cook to firm ball stage (without stirring) then add vanilla, nuts and salt.

title: orange drop cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream together shortening, butter and brown sugar. Beat in eggs, orange peel, orange juice, vanilla and buttermilk. Sift together dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Add nuts. Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove bones; add bouillon to hot broth.
Take one cup of broth, add egg and dry ingredients.
Use enough flour to make stiff.
Roll out and cut into strips.
Drop into hot boiling broth.
Cook until done, then add milk.
Let simmer.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Mix
all ingredients and pour into one long baking dish or 2 pie pans. Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Boil noodles in chicken broth and water until done.
Add soup and chicken.
Stir.
Cook on low heat for 10 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in an 8 X 8-inch pan.
Layer drained (save juice) peaches in pan.

title: candy bar brownies
directions: In a bowl, combine butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Set aside 1/4 cup of this dry mixture; add remaining dry ingredients to the egg mixture.
Mix well.
Toss Snickers bar pieces with reserved flour mixture; stir into batter.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Pour in batter and sprinkle milk chocolate candy bar pieces over top of batter. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Do not overbake.
Chill before cutting.
Can do ahead.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: fall salad
directions: Slice apples and celery. Combine with walnuts, grapes and marshmallows; toss. Combine mayonnaise, white sugar, lemon juice and coconut. Pour mixture over apples, etc.
Refrigerate for an hour, then serve cold!

title: beer batter
directions: Mix gently.
This is great batter for fried zucchini, onion rings, fried green tomatoes, etc.

title: lemon gooey bars
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 stick melted oleo, 1 egg and optional 1 tablespoon lemon juice; pat in bottom of 9 1/2 x 13 1/2-inch pan; set aside.
Using mixer, combine the second optional tablespoon of lemon juice and the box of powdered sugar.
Spread mixture on top of cake batter and bake 40 to 45 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.

title: finnish fried cookies
directions: Beat egg yolks for 20 minutes, until light and lemon colored. Add sugar gradually; beat for 15 minutes.
Add cream, whiskey, rind and cardamom.
Add flour and mix.
Make a stiff dough.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Turn dough out on lightly floured board and roll out to a 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut in diamond or other shapes.
Fry cookies until light brown in deep oil, heated to 360°. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: bacon wrapped hot dogs
directions: Boil hot dogs.
Drain and let cool.
Slice lengthwise almost through in the center.
Put a slice of cheese in each hot dog and a little prepared mustard.
Wrap bacon around hot dog.
Put in a casserole dish and sprinkle with Worcestershire Sauce.
Cover with foil and bake until brown.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and butter and mix well.
Then add oats, milk and coconut.
Makes 4 pies.
Bake in pie shell at 350°.

title: caramel dip for apples
directions: Beat cream cheese until soft; add rest of ingredients and blend until smooth.
Use as dip for apples.

title: coffee cake
directions: Note:
Do not grease or flour pan.

title: "grated apple pie"
directions: Melt margarine; stir sugar and flour mixture.
Stir in egg. Add apples and cinnamon.
Mix and pour into shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: tuscan tortellini soup
directions: Saute bacon and garlic for 5 to 8 minutes or until bacon is brown.
Remove from pan.
Cook spinach in pan drippings for 2 minutes or until wilted.
Stir in broth, beans, tomatoes and bell pepper and bring to a boil. Stir in pasta and bacon and simmer until pasta is al dente.

title: sopa de tortilla
directions: Cook chicken breasts until tender.
Bone and cut into large pieces.
Mix soups, onion and salsa together.
Layer tortilla strips, soup mixture and cheese in buttered 9 x 14-inch dish. Refrigerate 24 hours.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked fish and hush puppies
directions: Place large fish in roaster on rack and salt and pepper.
Mix 4 tablespoons mustard, 1/2 teaspoon lemon juice and enough water to cover bottom of roasting pan.
Pour mixture over fish.
Slice onions and put over fish.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until fish is flaky when pierced with fork.

title: polenta
directions: Mix polenta with cold water and stir well.
Boil 3 cups of water and add polenta in, stir and cook.
Stirring well, keep stirring until thick and cooked.
Serve polenta in a dish and add your favorite sauce on top. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: sweetheart salad
directions: Heat pineapple and sugar.
Dissolve gelatin with 1/4 cup water.
Add to pineapple and sugar mixture.
Mix lemon and cherry juice with cream cheese.
Add pecans and cherries to mixture. Whip cream and fold in.
Let stand at least 2 hours.

title: bill's macaroons
directions: Stir all together well until all is completely and thoroughly mixed.
It will be very stiff.
(The eggs are not beaten.)
Grease a cookie sheet lightly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls and top with 1/2 maraschino cherry.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until edges turn golden brown.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon; save 1/4 cup of juice.
Mix all ingredients and add juice a little at a time, as to make it not too runny.
Bake in a loaf pan at 375° for 1 hour, until brown.
Cool in pan.

title: grandma helen's hungarian chicken
directions: Chop onion and cook in oil with paprika and water.
Cover and simmer until tender.
Add flour to sour cream.
Bring to boil. Serve immediately over wide egg noodles or dumplings.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: In large bowl, mix sauerkraut, carrots, celery, green peppers, onion and pimientos.
In a small bowl, combine sugar and oil.
Pour over vegetables and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cube and boil eggplant.
Grate cheese and onion.
Add 3/4 of cheese to onion and eggs.
Mix together with eggplant.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Add the rest of the cheese to the top. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Cut potato into thin slices but do not cut through the bottom.
Put potatoes in a baking dish.
Fan them out. Mix spices and Parmesan cheese with melted butter.
Drizzle over potatoes.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake for another 10 minutes.
Check for doneness.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix spices, flour, salt and sugar well.
Add pumpkin and mix. Add slightly beaten eggs.
Scald milk and add to mixture.
Pour into unbaked crust.
Bake at 450° about 15 minutes until crust is set, then reduce heat to 300° and bake about 45 minutes until done.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix soup, sour cream and milk together.
Layer potatoes, soup mix, onions and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: italian rolls
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and seasonings.
Heat milk, water and butter until warm.
Add egg.
Blend at low speed until moistened.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, gradually stir in 1/2 cup cheese and flour to make a firm dough. Place in a greased bowl.
Cover; let rise in warm oven.
Punch down; divide into 16 pieces.
Form into balls.
Dip tops into 2 tablespoons butter and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Place in well-greased pan.
Cover; let rise.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove; let cool.

title: ice cream sauce
directions: Cook well until it starts to thicken.
Add brandy or sherry. Serve cold or hot on French vanilla ice cream.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and chill for pastry.
Beat or stir remaining ingredients with fork.

title: chicken breast supreme
directions: Wrap each piece of chicken in two slices of beef, then one slice of bacon.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Mix soup and sour cream together and pour over chicken.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake for 1/2 hour.
Serve with rice with sauce poured over.

title: bill's quick and easy chow mein(10-minute chow mein)
directions: Chop vegetables into bite-sized pieces.
Heat a large wok, then add oil.
Stir in vegetables and continue stirring for a few minutes.
Add garlic and continue stirring one minute.
Add mixture of water, soy sauce, ginger and cornstarch and cook on medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick and creamy.
Add meat if desired.
Serve over rice.

title: vegetable juice
directions: Wash everything clean without peeling skin.
Cut off any dirty parts.
Place all ingredients in pot with 3 gallons of water. Boil, then quickly simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Strain with
a clean towel.
Cool in refrigerator.
Enjoy.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Mash sweet potatoes. Add butter, sugar, milk, salt and orange rind. Scoop up 1/4 cup potato mixture and shape around each marshmallow (one tablespoon). Use more if necessary to cover. Roll each ball in crushed corn flakes or pecans. Place on buttered baking dish; cover with foil and freeze.

title: cinnamon apple rolls
directions: Combine flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, baking powder and salt. Add milk and 1/2 cup oil; stir just until dough holds together. Place on floured board and knead 10 to 12 strokes.
Roll to 1/4-inch thick.
Cover dough with combined apples, 1/2 cup brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up jelly roll fashion.
Cut into 1-inch thick pieces.
Combine 1 cup brown sugar, 1/2 cup oil and nuts in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Place rolls in pan.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Immediately turn upside-down onto platter. Makes 8 rolls.

title: mt. branson rocky road cake(the candlestick inn, mt. branson - branson, mo)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar, margarine and eggs.
Mix flour, salt and cocoa and add to sugar mixture.
Add vanilla, then fold in nuts and coconut.
Pour batter into a 13 x 18 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake in oven for 30 to 40 minutes, then top with marshmallow cream.
Pour Rocky Road Frosting over cake while still hot.
Top with whipping cream and chocolate sauce, if desired, before serving.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Place soup bone and beef in large pot.
Add water; bring to a boil.
Skim.
Add tomatoes, sauce, onions, salt and pepper; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Add celery and carrots; cover and simmer 1/2 hour.
Remove meat and bones; trim fat.
Cut meat into serving sizes and return to soup.
Heat to boiling.
Add uncooked pasta, green beans, peas and okra; simmer for 20 minutes.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Smush oleo in a 13 x 9-inch pan, lining pan with it.
Mix flour, sugar, milk and baking powder.
Pour in pan, lined with oleo.
Spoon in fruit.
(I use 1 large can and 1 small can.
You don't have to use that much if you prefer less peaches.
I like a lot!)
Bake in a 350° oven for about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: bacon-flavored dip mix(yield: 1 serving)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl; blend well.
Spoon mixture onto a 6-inch square of aluminum foil and fold to make airtight.
Label as Bacon-Flavored Dip Mix.
Store in a cool, dry place and use within 6 months.
Makes 1 package (about 3 tablespoons) of mix.

title: scalloped potatoes(great!)
directions: In baking dish, layer potatoes, salt and pepper, margarine and onion.
Cover with cheese.
Add 1 inch water.
Bake, covered, at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
It may be necessary to add more water, depending on potatoes.

title: banana sandwich
directions: Gently spread salad dressing or mayonnaise on a slice of bread.
Without tearing the bread, put peanut butter on the other slice.
Cut banana in chunks or long slices and place evenly on bread.
Put sandwich together, being very careful not to slobber until it reaches your delicate palate.
Hold the bottom together so as not to drop the banana chunks.

title: hot mulled punch
directions: Mix ahead of time (about 4 hours); bring to almost boil.
When ready to use, reheat (can reheat in coffeepot) and serve.
Very good in cold weather.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well.
Chill until good and cold.
Some suggested vegies are broccoli flower, whole mushrooms, carrots, or celery.

title: pizza cupcakes
directions: Mix cheeses and ground beef with pizza sauce.
Flatten rolls and put in cupcake pans.
Fill rolls with mixture.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.
Keep leftovers in refrigerator; reheat in microwave.

title: marshmallow date loaf
directions: Soak the marshmallows in the cream for 30 minutes. Add the dates, graham crackers and nuts. Form into a
roll about 3-inches in diameter. Place on wax paper. Chill for several hours or overnight. Slice and serve with whipped cream or applesauce.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Poach chicken breasts in chicken broth over medium heat 20 minutes.
Let cool in broth. Remove from broth.
Remove skin and bones from breasts and cut meat into 1/4-inch strips.
Crisp green onions in bowl of ice water.
Mix chicken, water chestnuts, sesame seed, pea pods and green onions in large bowl. Toss with as much Dijon-Sherry dressing as desired.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Makes 8 servings.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix and sift the dry ingredients; add the milk, then the well beaten egg, and last the melted butter.
Beat thoroughly.
Bake for 25 minutes in a shallow buttered pan in a hot oven.

title: buffet potatoes
directions: Mix all and bake in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: holiday potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes, unpeeled, until done; let cool.
Oil or butter a 9 X 13 casserole dish.
Shred potatoes into dish.
Heat Cheddar cheese, cream, milk, salt, mustard and nutmeg, being careful not to get too hot.
Pour over potatoes; sprinkle with paprika. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: santa fe corn soup
directions: Combine corn and broth in blender or food processor and puree. In 3-quart saucepan, combine butter and corn mixture.
Simmer slowly 5 minutes.
Add milk, garlic, oregano, salt and pepper and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and add chilies and chicken.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat, add cheese and baking soda (to prevent curdling), and stir until cheese is melted.
Ladle soup into bowls and top with tomatoes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer chopped cauliflower, add layer of chopped lettuce, add layer of 1/4 cup green pepper and layer of crumbled bacon.
Add a layer of shredded cheese.
Repeat layers.
Spread Miracle Whip over layered mix.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese and sprinkle sugar on layered mix.
Let set overnight.
Stir thoroughly before serving.

title: seafood macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni; drain well.
Add cooked seafood and rest of ingredients.
Mix in enough mayonnaise to moisten; 1/4 cup sweet pickles can be added.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Add remaining ingredients to ground beef and mix together well.
Form a loaf or loaves and place in baking dish or loaf pan(s).
Bake for approximately 1 hour in 350° oven.
Remove and cool for 5 to 10 minutes.
Slice and serve.

title: split pea soup
directions: In a six-quart kettle boil ham bone that still has some meat left, about 1/2 hour.Take meat from the bone and keep 2 quarts of the water.
Add 1 lb. yellow split peas (which have been rinsed), celery, onion and ham pieces to water and bring to boil, then simmer about 3 hours.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve hot.

title: five star soup
directions: Soak beans and cook with ham hock.
Add rest of ingredients to beans.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Add water as needed. Add smoked sausage, sliced, the last 20 to 30 minutes.

title: baked seafood casserole
directions: Mix together the crab meat, shrimp, mayonnaise, green peppers, onion, celery, salt and Worcestershire sauce. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Completely cover with crushed potato chips. Sprinkle with paprika, if desired. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serves 8.

title: crunchy chocolate fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips in a bowl in microwave.
Do not overcook chocolate!
Add peanuts and stir.
While still hot, stir in sweet milk and mix well.
Pour into a 8-inch pan lined with wax paper. Spread evenly; chill for 2 hours until firm.
Turn fudge out, peel off waxed paper and cut into squares.
You can do this without nuts also, it is very good either way.

title: chocolate layer delight
directions: Mix together and pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 30 minutes.
Let cool.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream butter in a mixing bowl.
Gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon. Gradually add to egg mixture.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Turn into a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve with hot buttered rum sauce.

title: french bread vegetable pizza
directions: * Add more or less to taste.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple and jello to boiling until jello dissolves. Set aside and add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Mix it all together and chill.

title: emy's pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Combine egg, water and vinegar.
Pour liquid into flour mixture.
Blend until moistened with a fork.
Makes 2 double crusts.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice eggplant thin.
Mix egg with a little milk.
Dip eggplant into egg mixture, then into bread crumbs.
Fry both sides for approximately 3 minutes total.
Then put into a greased casserole dish.
Cover with sauce and top with shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 1/2 to 1 hour, just until heated through.

title: plain muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Mix egg and milk, then oil, sugar and flour. Pour into greased muffin pan. Bake about 20 minutes.

title: oatmeal crisps
directions: Cream butter and sugars. Add vanilla and eggs.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful onto well-greased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Yields 14 dozen.

title: grandma chasteen's date pudding
directions: Cook all except nuts for 20 minutes.
Add nuts.
Pour into serving dish.
Cool.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: hungarian meatballs and sauerkraut
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Season meat with salt and pepper. Shape into balls.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes.

title: debbie field's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients but do not overbeat.
If dough is sticky, put in refrigerator to cool before baking.
Drop by spoonfuls. Bake on silver cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: big thicket dumplings
directions: Mix flour and salt with enough water to make a dough you can handle.
Roll out very thin on floured surface.
Cut in squares and drop into hot chicken broth.
Cook, without stirring, 15 minutes or until done.

title: layered salad
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Mix sugar and mayonnaise and spread on top.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Cover; do not mix. Refrigerate for 8 to 12 hours.
Mix before serving.

title: special rice
directions: Add juices to water to make 1 cup of liquid.
Combine all ingredients in casserole dish.
Cover tightly and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: slumgolium
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Brown hamburger and onions; drain. Mix mushroom soup and milk in with hamburger and onions.
Add cheese from macaroni and cheese box.
Stir well.
Add any optionals.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes over medium heat.
Serves 6.

title: charcoaled ham steak
directions: Set charcoal 45 minutes to 1 hour before time to begin grilling.
Place ham on slightly greased grill over hot coals.
Mix all other ingredients.
Baste ham frequently with sauce.
Grill 5 to 7 minutes per side until steak is rich and brown color.
Serve remaining sauce with ham.
Serves 6.

title: aunt sandie's quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Fry bacon.
Crumble in bottom of pie shell.
Mix eggs, cream, salt and nutmeg together.
Add Swiss cheese.
Pour over bacon bits into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then turn oven back to 325° and bake for 35 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine dry onion soup and water; beat in eggs with fork.
Add meat and mix well.
Shape mixture into meatballs.
Combine sauerkraut, cranberry sauce, chili sauce and brown sugar.
Pour half into bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Set remaining mixture aside.

title: beef porcupines
directions: Mix beef, rice, onion powder and seasonings.
Form into small balls.
Fry in oil, turning frequently until light brown, but not crusty, on all sides.
Add sauce and water.
Mix well.
Cover and simmer about 45 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add beaten eggs; stir in pumpkin. Sift dry ingredients together and beat slowly into creamed mixture.

title: potato candy
directions: Cook potatoes to be mashed, adding only a little salt.
To 1/2 cup of mashed potatoes, add 1/2 teaspoon of vanilla and 1 pound of 10x sugar.
Make up like a stiff dough, then spread on a piece of wax paper.
On this potato mixture, spread 1 cup of peanut butter, then roll up and chill.
Slice to look like pinwheels.

title: florida dump cake
directions: Spread fruits in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly over fruit.
Slice margarine evenly over cake mix. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: jerry orback's guiltless french fries
directions: Prepare the night before serving:
Pour olive oil or vegetable oil into a measuring cup.
Add red and green chili peppers and bay leaf.
Cover and refrigerate overnight to flavor oil.

title: apricot glazed chicken
directions: Mix dressing, preserves and soup mix in small pan.
Bring to boil.
Cool slightly.
Pour over chicken in shallow baking dish. Marinate for several hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: chocolate chip muffins
directions: *Egg product may be used in place of whole egg.

title: play dough
directions: Mix dry ingredients in big pot.
Blend all liquids together. Pour into dry ingredients; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat when dough pulls away from sides of pot and can be pinched without sticking (about 5 minutes).
Turn onto counter; knead until smooth.
Store in airtight container. Pastel colors make better colors.
Keeps up to a year.
If it becomes sticky, add a little flour.

title: miracle fruit cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, boil gently for 3 minutes.
Cool in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients gradually beating well after each addition.
Pour into a 9-inch well-greased tube pan. Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours or until baked completely.

title: grandmother's pralines
directions: Peel grapefruit and cut in small strips.
Cook them three times in water, bringing it to a boil each time.
(This helps take the bitterness out of the peel.)
Make syrup by using equal parts of water and sugar (approximately 1 cup of sugar to 2 grapefruit). Add grapefruit and cook until transparent.
Put in colander to drain.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Let dry about 24 to 48 hours. To test: Bend peels on plate.
It remains bent, it is done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken in large chunks (no skin).
Add celery, peppers, onions, cream of mushroom soup (do not add water to soup), mayonnaise, water chestnuts and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Put in casserole dish.
Cook 15 minutes at 350°.
Vegetables will be crunchy.
Take out of oven.
Place French fried onions over it. Put back in oven; cook for 5 minutes.
Serve hot.
This is most delicious.

title: chocolate coconut bars
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and butter; press onto the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Cool. Combine coconut and milk; spread over crust.
Bake an additional 15 minutes.
Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Spread over top.
Allow to set before cutting.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients in ice cream churn.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add to casserole dish with other ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Put cooked broccoli into greased baking dish and add other ingredients except crumbs.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: sunshine carrots
directions: Slice carrots on bias about 1-inch thick.
Cook in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain.
In another saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, salt and ginger.
Add orange juice slowly, stirring constantly, until it thickens.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in margarine.
Pour over hot cooked carrots.

title: patty's cole slaw
directions: Over cabbage, spread onion, pepper and sugar.
Boil oil and vinegar.
Add spices.
Pour over all.
Cover; allow to marinate overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: hot bean dish in tomato sauce
directions: We were told the dam was going to flood us and we had to move. They cut off the garage, cut up the house, put it on trucks, and moved to where it is now in Mt. Mesa.

title: hot potatoes
directions: Quarter potatoes in a large pan.
Saute onion in butter and pour over
potatoes.
Crumble toasted bread onto potatoes. Quarter cheese and put on top of toasted bread.
Crumble bacon and
put on top of
cheese.
Cook
at
until
cheese
is bubbly.

title: cracked sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 305°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Cream sugar and butter until light in color.
Beat in yolks and vanilla. Sift measured, sifted flour, baking soda and cream of tartar. Fold into butter-sugar mix.
Form dough into balls, the size of a cherry.
Place 2-inches apart on cookie sheet.
Do not flatten. Bake about 11 minutes until tops are cracked and cookie is just turning color.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: crab burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding crab meat last.
Save 1 cup of cheese.
Spread on lightly toasted hamburger buns. Sprinkle with additional cheese.
Broil until lightly brown and bubbly.
Serve immediately.

title: oatmeal candy
directions: Combine sugar, butter, cocoa and milk. Boil 1 1/2 minutes; mix in oats. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: luscious lemon
directions: Combine all ingredients, except zest, in a bowl; beat with mixer until fluffy (about 3 minutes). Stir in zest. Pour mixture over hot crust and bake for 20 minutes (to check if it is done, lightly touch center and look for it to spring back). Remove from oven and run a knife around the edges. Sift powdered sugar over the top. Refrigerate for 4 hours before cutting. Makes forty-eight 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: ritz chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done and remove from bone.
Cut into small pieces.
Place on bottom of casserole dish.
Combine sour cream and soup; spread over chicken.
Crush crackers and mix with poppy seed.
Spread over soup mixture.
Melt butter and drizzle over top of crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: frogmore stew
directions: Bring large pot of water to boil (twice as much water as ingredients).
Add 1/4 cup salt per gallon of water.
Add seasonings, celery and onion.
Add sausage; boil 7 minutes.
Add corn; boil 7 minutes.
Add shrimp; boil 4 minutes.
Drain and serve in large bowl or tub.
Serves a crowd.

title: lima beans and sausage
directions: In 2 quarts of water, cook lima beans until beans are tender. Drain water in colander; place limas in 2-quart casserole dish. Add tomatoes and top with sausage.
Cover and cook at 300° for about 1 hour then uncover and cook 15 minutes more to brown sausage.
Serve.

title: acapulco delight
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Stir in taco seasoning, adding water according to package directions.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Place 2 tortillas in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread 1/2 of meat mixture over tortillas and sprinkle with 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese.
Top with 2 more tortillas.
Spread with refried beans. Cover with 1 1/2 cups sour cream.
Place 2 remaining tortillas over mixture and cover with remaining meat mixture and Cheddar cheese. Top with Monterey Jack cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until bubbly.
Remove from oven and top with lettuce, tomatoes and 1/2 cup sour cream.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch) loaf pans. In large bowl with fork, mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. In medium bowl with fork, beat eggs; slightly stir in salad oil, zucchini and lemon peel.
Stir liquid mix into flour mix just until flour is blended well.
Pour into pans.
Bake 1 hour.
Cool on wire racks for 10 minutes; remove from pans.

title: broccoli appetizers(serves 12)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll in balls.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: little applesauce muffins
directions: In a large bowl, cream the butter and sugar until fluffy. Beat in eggs, then add applesauce and rest of ingredients.
Stir just enough to moisten.
Put in muffin cups and bake in preheated oven at 425° for about 15 minutes or until golden.

title: double chocolate nuggets
directions: Blend cake mix, oil and eggs.
Stir in chocolate pieces.
Drop from a teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: praline cheesecake
directions: To make praline, caramelize 1 cup sugar; stir in pecans and immediately spread onto greased baking sheet.
When cool, break into small pieces and chop in food processor or blender.
Do not pulverize completely.
Combine crumbs with butter in food processor or blender.
Press into 9-inch spring-form pan.
Beat eggs; add softened cream cheese, 1 cup sugar, salt and vanilla. Beat until smooth.
Fold in sour cream, then crushed praline. Bake at 375° about 35 minutes or just until set.
Chill 4 to 5 hours or overnight.
Serves 12.

title: chocolate candy
directions: Mix margarine, milk, confectioners sugar and vanilla until creamy and smooth.
Shape into small balls.
Melt together wax and chocolate.
Dip balls into hot mixture.
Place a pecan half on top of each at once.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Add corn and other ingredients.
Pour into greased 6 cups casserole.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes or until golden brown and set in center at 350° oven.

title: company strata
directions: Cut each slice of bread with a donut cutter, or use small and large glass.
You will have 12 donuts with holes.
Use the scraps to line bottom of 13 x 9 x 2 1/2-inch ungreased baking pan.
Layer with 6 slices cheese, 1 package broccoli and 1 cup ham.
Cover layer with donuts and holes.
Repeat.
Combine eggs, milk, onion, salt and mustard; pour over ingredients in pan.
Refrigerate 6 hours.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Break cake into small pieces into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour strawberries over cake and mix well.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: best carrot cake
directions: Line 3 (9-inch) round cake pans with wax paper; lightly grease and flour wax paper.
Stir together first 4 ingredients.
Beat eggs and next 4 ingredients at medium speed.
Add flour mixture, beating at low speed until blended.
Fold in carrots and next 3 ingredients.
Pour into prepared cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Drizzle Buttermilk Glaze evenly over layers.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan; remove from heat. Add cocoa, sugar, eggs, salt, flour and vanilla. Beat well.
Pour into a well-greased 9-inch pie pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Cool.
Serve plain or top with whipped cream or ice cream, if desired.
If served warm, spoon into compotes.
If chilled, cut into wedges.
Makes 6 servings.

title: shrimp ball or log
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
From ball or log.
Place in container and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: almond tea
directions: Boil water, sugar, juice of 1 lemon and 1/2 lemon rind together for 5 minutes and then remove rind.
Add juice of 2 lemons, brewed tea, almond extract and vanilla extract.
Keeps well in refrigerator.
Serve hot.

title: awesome carrot cake!
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs, drained pineapple, vanilla and carrots.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture. Add nuts and raisins.
Bake in very lightly greased 9 x 15-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: finger paint
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan and add water.
Cook over low heat, stirring all the time, about 5 minutes.
Remove from stove.
Cool and pour into plastic or paper cups.
Add a drop of detergent to each cup along with food coloring.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Dissolve first
three
ingredients
in a small bowl and let sit
for
10 minutes.
Mix remaining water, honey, vanilla and salt
in
separate
bowl.
Fold in flour, warm blueberries and nuts.
Put into sprayed muffin tins.
Let rise 10 minutes. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Tie up spices and cinnamon in a piece of cheesecloth.
Mix brown sugar and apple cider together.
Pour into pan and place bag of spices in liquid.
Let simmer at least 1 hour prior to serving. Double recipe for use in crock-pot.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cover the bottom of a 9x13 baking dish with Doritos. (Save some for the top) Layer chicken on top of Doritos. Melt Velveeta. Next add cream of chicken soup and RoTels to Velveeta and pour over layered chicken. Sprinkle with garlic, then add remaining Doritos. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: curried vegetables
directions: Use a large soup pot and saute onion, garlic and oil until tender.
Add the next 8 ingredients to the onion and garlic mixture.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until zucchini is tender.
You can also add broccoli.
Serve with rice or serve plain.
This makes a large quantity, so plan on leftovers unless you are having a party or feeding a family of eight.

title: pickled beets
directions: Remove stems and leaves from beets and wash thoroughly.
Cook beets, covered, in water until they are slightly tender, but not real soft.
Pour water off, cool and peel beets.
After they are cooled, quarter or slice beets and if they are real small, you can leave them whole.
Place them in jars, have flats and rings of jars hot.
Mix sugar and vinegar in pan and bring to a good boil.
Pour over beets that are in the jars and add salt according to the size of the jar.
Place flats and rings on jars.
Place in water bath cooker until hot.
Remove from cooker, cover, until cooled and sealed.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt margarine in medium pan, pour in the graham cracker crumbs and mash together to make a layer.
Cover layer with Eagle Brand milk.
Layer chocolate chips, coconut and almonds.
Press down gently.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: danny boy's seafood marinara
directions: In a large frypan add your mushrooms, onion, green pepper, bay leaves, garlic and stewed tomatoes and saute in butter with a little taste of white wine.
Simmer on low heat.
While this is simmering, steam your seafood.
Can be done together but do not add seasonings.
When steamed, add this to the pasta sauce.
You may shell your shrimp and mussels.
When you feel the vegetables have simmered enough, add all ingredients together and simmer for another 10 to 15 minutes and serve over your pasta.
You may add just a touch of sugar to take the bite out of the sauce.
Serve with a small salad, garlic bread, a white wine, candlelight and good conversation.
Guarantee a pleasant dinner.

title: oatmeal butterscotch cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: herb dip with asparagus
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature, then mix all ingredients.
Add sour cream and mix until creamy.

title: frosty strawberry squares
directions: Stir together flour, brown sugar, nuts and butter.
Spread in shallow pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Combine egg whites, sugar, berries and lemon juice.
Beat at high speed to stiff peaks (about 10 minutes).
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon over baked crust and freeze 6 hours or overnight.
Cut into squares.
Makes 24.

title: chow chow relish
directions: Chop all vegetables; sprinkle with salt and let stand for 12 hours.
Then drain.
Simmer vinegar and spices for 10 minutes. Remove the sack of cloves.
Then add vegetables and simmer for 10 minutes until boiling.
Then pour into hot clean jars and seal. Water bath for 5 minutes, counting time from when the water starts boiling.

title: french toast
directions: Beat egg with milk.
Add sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt. Soak both sides of bread in this mixture for a couple of minutes. Fry in melted butter or shortening until naturally brown on both sides.
Serve with powdered sugar.

title: rocky road bars
directions: Arrange in wax paper lined pan the marshmallows.
Fill spaces between with broken walnuts or Post Toasties cereal.
Cover with melted chocolate, cool until hard.
Cut into squares.

title: fudge oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook sugar, cocoa, Pet milk and butter for 5 minutes.
Add oats and cook 3 minutes.
Add flavoring and beat unti creamy. Drop on wax paper.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Form in ball.
Roll in nuts and chill.

title: verdas
directions: Soak split peas overnight in enough water to cover.
Place the soaked peas in a blender or food processor and grind to form a coarse paste.
Add water sparingly when needed.
Pour paste in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.

title: white fruit cake(by louise hubbard, a friend)
directions: Pour one cup light wine over fruits. Let stand overnight. Prepare tube cake pan.
Beat eggs until a lemon color.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients together twice.
Alternately beat flour and eggs into creamed mixture, beginning and ending with flour, using a wooden spoon and a strong arm, not an electric beater.
Stir all remaining ingredients into batter.
Bake 2 1/2 or 3 hours, depending on the size of the pan. Test by inserting a toothpick which should come out dry.
Cool in the pan on a rack.
For storage, wrap tightly in plastic paper and again in aluminum foil.
The cake keeps for months.

title: meringue puffs
directions: Beat egg whites and salt, adding sugar a little at a time. Beat until mixture is very stiff.
Add cream of tartar and fold in chocolate chips and flavoring. Preheat oven to 375° for 15 minutes.
Drop cookies on ungreased cookie sheets.
Turn off oven. Put cookies in oven and leave overnight or at least 6 hours.
(Do not open oven.)
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: fried bread
directions: We all think that Matt makes the very best pancakes. He always made pancakes for us on a weekend, either Saturday or Sunday.
And when we go to visit him, we ask for his pancakes.
What a treat!

title: low-fat meatless chili
directions: Mix all ingredients in a pot.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese balls
directions: In medium size mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth and fluffy.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill 30 to 45 minutes. Divide mixture and shape into 2 balls.
Cover with transparent wrap.
Chill for several hours or overnight.
May be frozen.

title: grandma heath's rhubarb cream pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add sugar and lemon juice and rind. Chill to consistency of egg white.
Fold in rhubarb and cream. When partially set, pour into baked 10-inch pie shell and chill thoroughly.

title: taco casserole
directions: Cook ground chuck and onions on high for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring every minute or so.
Drain grease.
Add seasoning mix, tomato sauce and beans and mix well.
Spread corn chips in bottom of casserole.
Pour meat mixture over chips.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove.
Sprinkle cheese and bake until cheese melts.

title: rhubarb strawberry pie
directions: Combine eggs, butter, rhubarb and strawberries.
Mix sugar, cinnamon, salt and flour.
Dice rhubarb and berries.
Add to fruit; blend well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 375°.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except onions, in casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with onions and bake 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chili con carne
directions: Heat pressure cooker; add shortening.
Add ground beef, breaking it apart and searing it until browned.
Add onions, garlic and diced pepper.
Brown lightly.
Stir in tomatoes, kidney beans, salt, cayenne pepper and chili powder.
Place cover on pressure cooker.
Allow steam to flow from vent pipe and cook 15 minutes at cook position.
Let stem return to down position.

title: tuna burger
directions: Fluff tuna with a fork; place in a medium bowl.
Add celery, onion and cheese; mix.
Add mayonnaise, salt and pepper; mix well again.
Fill buns with tuna mixture; replace tops.
Heat in paper sandwich bags on baking sheet in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
With fork or knife, poke holes in top of cake all over the top while cake is still warm.
In a small bowl, mix the cream of coconut and Eagle Brand and pour over the warm cake, letting it seep into the holes.
Let this cool and top with Cool Whip and coconut.
This is so moist and delicious!

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni, drain and cool.
Add vegetables and mix well. Combine milk, vinegar, sugar, mayo, salt and pepper; add to vegetable mixture.
Mix thoroughly and chill at least four hours before serving.
Overnight is better.
Mixture will be extra juicy in beginning but will be absorbed.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix cornbread crumbs, salt and sugar.
Beat eggs until very light.
Stir in milk and add to corn mixture.
Turn into well-buttered baking dish.
Dot with bits of butter and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix all together and roll out.
Add your favorite fruit and bake as directed.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Blend ingredients well (except wafers and pie filling). Place 1 vanilla wafer in a cupcake cup.
Spoon in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: taco dip
directions: Cook and drain ground beef.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat through in crockpot.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and set aside.
Melt butter or margarine in a saucepan over medium heat. Add onion and cook for 1 minute.
Stir in flour.
Remove from heat and stir in dry mustard, salt, Worcestershire sauce and pepper. Slowly stir in milk.
Cook over medium-low heat, stirring constantly until mixture is smooth and comes to a boil.
Add cheese and stir over low heat until cheese is melted and sauce is smooth.
Combine sauce and macaroni.
Turn into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake about 20 minutes or until hot at 400°.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: perky tuna dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Serve as a dip or topping for baked potatoes, vegetables or chips.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on box.
While noodles are cooking, beat egg yolk and add to cream.
Melt butter, place drained hot noodles in warm serving bowl or platter.
Pour egg and cream mixture, melted butter and 1/2 of the Parmesan cheese over noodles.
Toss noodles until well blended adding remaining cheese gradually while tossing.
Serve immediately.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter; mix in flour to make paste.
Put corn in baking dish; add cream and flour mixture to corn.
Stir to mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cookie cutter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add in egg and vanilla; mix well. Sift together dry ingredients and add in, mixing well.
Chill at least 1/2 hour.
Roll half of the dough on a lightly floured surface until 1/8 or 1/4-inch thick.
The thinner you roll the dough the crisper the cookie.
Cut into whatever shapes you like. Reroll scrapes.
Bake at 325° for 8 minutes until lightly browned. Cool on newspaper to absorb excess grease.
When cool, frost as you like.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Heat in double boiler until cheese is melted.
Add 1 small carton of sour cream.
Pour in casserole.
Cover with 1 cup crumbled corn flakes and some melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spinach salad
directions: In large bowl, layer ingredients:
1/2 spinach, 1/2 peas, 1/2 eggs.
Separate onion rings.
Mix Miracle Whip and sour cream. Spread over top.
Seal edges.
Sprinkle cheese over top, cover and refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle bacon on top before mixing. Serve.

title: turkey rose
directions: Melt butter; saute onion until tender.
Stir in flour; add broth and wine.
Cook until thick.
Add turkey, mushrooms, peas, almonds and pepper.
Heat through.
Serve over rice.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Cook 20 minutes, stirring at all times.
Remove from heat and add 2 beaten egg yolks.
Return to heat and cook 2 more minutes. Put in pie shell and let set.

title: company casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; add salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Simmer 30 minutes in tomato sauce.
Mix sour cream, cream cheese and cottage cheese well with fork.
Add chopped onions and mix.
Cook noodles as directed on package; drain and add 2 tablespoons butter.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Combine all ingredients together and spread thin onto tortillas. Roll up and chill. Cut into spirals and serve with salsa.

title: 2 crust or 10-inch pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and oil with fork, then add cold water, mixing with fork to form ball. Using hands, mix a little before rolling out between 2 sheets of wax paper.
Do not double recipe.
No flour on waxed paper. Bake crust at 475° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pickled onion appetizers
directions: Cut
each
cake
of cream cheese into 12 squares with a piece of	string.
Let
stand at room temperature until soft. Roll squares of cheese into ball.
Press a hole in the center and stuff
with
well drained pickled onions.
Reshape cheese into ball and roll in any of last ingredients.
Chill at least 1 hour. Makes 24 appetizers.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Melt margarine. Add onion and cook until tender. Add milk and cheese.
Heat until cheese melts. In a large casserole dish, place broccoli and cooked rice.
Pour soup mixture over and mix lightly. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
May top with cheese slices.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jell-O in boiling water.
Let cool.
Add strawberries, pineapple, cranberry sauce and pecans.
Put in 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan or mold sprayed with cooking spray.
Cover and chill until firm.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Put all ingredients through blender or food chopper, except nuts and sugar.
Combine all and mix well.	This is delicious with chicken and dressing.
Keeps well in refrigerator for several days.

title: cheese cake squares
directions: Combine cake mix, 1 egg and margarine; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat powdered sugar with cream cheese and remaining eggs.
Pour over cake mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool then cut into squares.

title: turkey fruit salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, honey and ginger; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Season with salt lightly, if desired. Chill.
Add additional mayonnaise before serving, if desired.

title: lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles as directed on package. Drain and rinse in cold water.
In frypan, break apart ground beef and cook until browned, stirring occasionally.
Drain fat.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and bring to a boil; remove from heat.
Assemble lasagna in a 13 x 9-inch pan by layering 1/3 noodles, 1/3 meat sauce, 1/2 of cottage cheese and 1/2 of Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat with next layer.
On last layer of noodles, spread with sauce and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 35 to 40 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pol's apple cake
directions: Blend eggs, oil and sugar until creamy.
Add flour a little at a time.
Blend well.
Batter will be stiff.
Fold in apples, coconut and nuts.
Pour into tube pan and bake for 1 hour.
Remove from pan after about 30 minutes.
Top warm cake with topping.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well and add milk, then flour.
Beat well as you add flour and baking powder; flavor to taste with vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on well-greased cookie sheet.

title: banana split pie(makes two pies)
directions: Cream margarine and powdered sugar.
Add eggs and beat at high speed for 20 minutes. Pour filling into crusts. Slice bananas in thirds lengthwise and dip in lemon juice.
Arrange on top of filling.
Spread sliced strawberries on top of bananas.
Cover fruit with Cool Whip (1 small one for each pie).
Cover and refrigerate at least one hour.

title: raisin bar cookies
directions: Cook raisins in enough water to have 1 cup juice.
Simmer at least 10 minutes.
Cool.
Stir together brown sugar, margarine, egg and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir together the dry ingredients.
Add raisin juice to sugar mixture and mix well.
Add flour and mix, then add the raisins and nuts.
Spread in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Frost with powdered sugar icing.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Best if allowed to be refrigerated for a day or so before serving.

title: yellow party punch
directions: Serves 45 punch cups.

title: baked orange french toast
directions: Butter a 9-inch square pan.
Lay bread slices evenly in pan. Combine orange peel, orange juice, eggs, liqueur, half and half and granulated sugar.
Pour over bread.
Dot with butter if desired.
Refrigerate.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Cut kraut.
Mix all ingredients
well
and put in a jar to keep.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach and drain well (mash out juice). Mix all other ingredients with spinach and refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar, milk and egg in bowl.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in bottom of dish.
Add fruit.
Bake in a 350° oven until done.

title: apple nut squares
directions: Blend eggs, sugar and oil.
Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon together.
Stir into egg mixture.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake in a lightly greased pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool; cut in squares.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar if desired.

title: chocolate sponge cake
directions: Per Serving:
96 calories, 3 grams protein, 2 grams fat and 17 grams carbohydrates.

title: crab casserole
directions: Thaw macaroni; mix all together and put in large casserole. Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.
May top with crumbs if desired.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti until done.
Drain and rinse with cool water. Pour into bowl.
Dice tomatoes and drain well.
Chop green peppers and onions.
Pour over spaghetti.
Dash 1/2 bottle of Salad Supreme.
Pour dressing on, toss and chill.

title: sweet 'n sour pork
directions: Brown
pork in 1 tablespoon oil, 1 tablespoon soy sauce and
1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce.
Add 1/2 cup water and simmer 1/2
hour.	Remove	cooked	pork
from
skillet; add 1 tablespoon oil
to
skillet along with green peppers, onions, 1/2
teaspoon soy sauce and 1/2 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce. Saute lightly. Add cooked pork, pineapple tidbits, maraschino cherries, pineapple
juice,
brown
sugar,
cornstarch, cider vinegar
and sweet and sour sauce.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes. Serve with rice.

title: danish pastry apple bars
directions: Combine flour and salt; cut in margarine and shortening.
Beat egg yolk; add enough milk to make 2/3 cup liquid.
Mix well; add to flour mixture.
Roll half dough into 17 x 12-inch rectangle. Fit into 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle corn flakes on dough; top with apples.
Combine sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over apples.
Roll out remaining dough and place over top; seal and slit in several places.
Beat egg white until frothy and brush over crust.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Combine powdered sugar with milk; drizzle over hot pastry.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and buttermilk.
Add next 3 ingredients. Mix well and pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350 degrees for about 30 minutes.

title: martha's salad
directions: Mix rice and vegetables and let set overnight in refrigerator. Mix Hidden Valley Ranch dressing with mayonnaise and milk as directed on package.
Let stand overnight.
Mix before serving.

title: cranberry cake pie
directions: Place this mixture in greased 9-inch pie plate and pour batter on.

title: dietetic lime mist cheesecake
directions: Crush graham crackers.
In large bowl, mix crackers and melted diet margarine.
Let mixture cool briefly, then mix in nonfat margarine.
Press mixture onto bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch pan, reserving 1/4 to 1/3 cup for crumbling over the top.
In large bowl or in blender, mix cream cheese, Jell-O, D-Zerta, sweetener and 2 cups boiling water on high for at least 3 minutes after cream cheese and Jell-O have dissolved by the mixing.
Let cool briefly. Pour into pan.
Refrigerate until jelled.
Crumble remaining crumbs over top.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the broccoli flowerets, drained and sliced water chestnuts, raisins and crumbled bacon,
In a separate bowl, mix together the mayonnaise, sugar and white vinegar. Add the dressing mixture to the broccoli mixture and chill in the refrigerator at least 4 hours.
Will keep for at least a week.

title: bess' never fail fudge
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in 4 quart saucepan.
Stir over low heat until blended.
Bring to boil over moderate heat, being careful not to mistake escaping air bubbles for boiling.
Then boil slowly, stirring constantly for 5 minutes (to soft ball stage).
Remove from heat, stir in chocolate and vanilla (and nuts if used) until chocolate is melted.
Pour into 2 buttered 9 x 9-inch pans and cool.
Makes about 5 pounds.

title: peanut butter oatmeal bars
directions: Stir together flour, sugar and peanut butter; mix in eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add oats and mix well.
Spread in lightly greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 375°
for 12 to 15 minutes. Cool; spread with peanut butter frosting.
Cut into bars.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Combine wet ingredients except chopped turkey.
Mix dry ingredients together, including spices.
In a mixing bowl, add wet ingredients to chopped turkey.
Then add dry ingredients. Lightly grease loaf pan and place mixture inside.
Cook for 40-45 minutes at 350 F.
Fork will come out dry when done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups and broth.
Melt butter and mix with stuffing. Press thin layer of stuffing in greased casserole; then chicken, then broth and soup mixture.
Repeat.
(Reserve a small amount of stuffing to sprinkle on top.)
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: vegetable spread
directions: Combine vegetables and drain well on paper towels.
Soften gelatin in cold water.
Add boiling water and cool.
Fold in mayonnaise and salt.
Add vegetables and pour into lightly oiled mold.
Chill until firm.
Serve with crackers.

title: beef nachos casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat; drain.
Stir in salsa, corn, dressing and chili powder.
Layer 1/2 of meat mix, chips and cheese in a casserole dish.
Repeat layers.
Bake 20 minutes.
Top with lettuce and tomatoes, if wanted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bill's awesome sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger.
Brown onion and pepper separately.
Combine hamburger, onion and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes, stirring regularly.
Thicken if desired.
Serve on open-faced buns.

title: good eating
directions: In an iron skillet put two teaspoons of bacon drippings, and sprinkle a little corn meal in it.
Let it get hot.
Mix corn meal, milk, cream corn and baking soda.
Pour half of mixture in skillet. Top that mixture with your hamburg.
Slice onion and place over hamburg.
Add jalapeno peppers to your taste.
Sprinkle on top, 2 cups of shredded cheddar cheese.
Then pour remaining batter over that.
Bake about 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: rhubarb slush
directions: Cook rhubarb and water until tender; strain (throw away rhubarb pulp).
While still hot, add Jell-O, lemon juice and sugar.
Put in container and freeze.
Serve 2 scoops or more of slush in a glass with 7-Up or ginger ale.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup of warm water. Mix shortening, flour and sugar with other cup of water. Add cup of dissolved yeast last. Let rise about 2 hours. Cook at 400°.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet and flatten.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: zucchini impossible pie
directions: Slice or dice zucchini, tomatoes and onion.
Place in a greased 10-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix in blender the milk, Bisquick, eggs, salt and pepper.
Pour over top and bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
(You may add any kind of meat.)

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix milk and Cool Whip together.
Blend in other ingredients and refrigerate.

title: curried shrimp on rice
directions: Blend butter, flour and seasoning.
Gradually stir in milk. Cool until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
Add the rest of the ingredients, except rice.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve over mounds of fluffy hot rice.
Serves 6.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

title: mom's chicken biscuit stew
directions: Preheat oven
to
In 9 x 13-inch pan melt margarine; blend in flour, salt and pepper on stove.
Add broth and milk, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add chicken, onion and vegetables
(broccoli
can
be
substituted
for peas) and simmer until hot and bubbly.
Separate biscuits and place over mixture. Bake
to 25 minutes or until biscuits are nicely browned. Makes about 4 servings.

title: aunt lea's pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat well.
Bake in bundt pan 1 1/2 hours at 325° or in 3 loaf pans for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: curried dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Serve with assorted raw vegetables.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion; pour off grease and put in bottom of rectangular baking dish.
Add green beans. Mix together soup and milk.
Arrange Tater Tots on green beans; pour soup and milk mixture over all.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour.

title: bruschetta
directions: Toast bread; set aside.
Combine tomato, onion, parsley, vinegar, oil, salt and oregano with pepper.
Let stand 10 minutes. Spoon tomato mixture over top of toasted bread.

title: pico de gallo
directions: Chop and mix. Refrigerate. Use as dip or topping on potatoes.

title: oven barbecue chicken
directions: In a glass baking dish, bake chicken at 350° for 30 minutes; drain off grease.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken. Return to oven and bake
an additional 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lo-cal tomato dressing
directions: In a covered jar or shaker, combine ingredients and chill. Shake well before using.
Serve on salad greens.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: veal shanks
directions: Coat 4 pieces of
veal shanks with flour.
Heat cooking oil in heavy skillet
and add minced garlic clove.
Add shanks and
brown on
both
sides.
Add
chopped
onion
and chopped carrots.
Add celery,
tomatoes,	bay
leaves and white wine. Cook
slowly
1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle
with parsley and grated lemon peel.
Serve with rice or spaghetti. Makes 4 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Optional:
Use 3 cups self-rising flour and nuts.

title: sunday sausage breakfast
directions: In a skillet, brown sausage; drain.
In a greased 13-inch x 9-inch x 2-inch baking dish, layer the croutons, sausage, and cheese.
Combine eggs and milk and mix well.
Pour over the cheese.
Sprinkle with basil, salt, and pepper.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: beef 'n cream 'n nut spread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except for walnuts (can be done more easily in a food processor).
Spread in quiche dish or large pie plate.
Top with chopped walnuts.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°. Serve hot with crackers or French bread cubes.

title: refrigerator muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over Bran Buds and set aside to cool. Cream Crisco and sugar; add beaten eggs, buttermilk and cooked bran mixture.
Add Bran Flakes, soda and salt.
Fold in flour just until all is moistened.
Place in refrigerator until ready to use. (Stores 6 to 8 weeks in refrigerator.)
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes in greased muffin tins.

title: judy's chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; put in greased glass baking dish.
Top with 1 cup plain bread crumbs and 3 tablespoons oleo.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spanish hamburgers
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; add chopped pepper and remaining ingredients. Simmer. Serve on hamburger buns.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Bake cake in cookie sheet with 1-inch sides, greased and floured 15 to 20 minutes.

title: egg in a frame
directions: Put margarine on one side of bread.
Cut a 1 1/2 to 2-inch hole in the middle of the bread.
Put margarine side down in a small skillet.
Crack egg; pour into hole.
Cover and cook on medium heat until egg is cooked through.
Flip and cook for a few seconds.
Also cook the hole.
Serve.
Kids love this!

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
May be served chilled or at room temperature.

title: christmas wreaths
directions: Melt the butter and marshmallows over low heat.
Add green food coloring to marshmallow mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and blend.
While still warm, drop by heaping tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper; form into wreaths.
(Dip fingertips in bowl of cold water to prevent sticking.)
Decorate with red hots (candy) to appear as a Christmas wreath.

title: peppered steak
directions: Press freshly ground pepper into both sides of filets. Salt the beef to taste.

Heat butter and olive oil in a large skillet. Dissolve bouillon cube in water. When butter and oil are at frying temperature, sear filets on both sides, then cook for about 5 minutes on each side. Put meat on heated platter. Add bouillon to skillet. Stir and scrape to deglaze the pan. Pour sauce over filets and serve immediately.

title: old fashioned gingerbread
directions: Beat butter until soft.
Beat in egg.
Add light molasses; mix well.
Sift flour, soda, salt, ginger, cinnamon and cloves onto wax paper.
Add to molasses mixture alternately with hot water.

title: hot dogs on a stick
directions: Sift first 6 ingredients in a bowl.
Mix in corn meal.
Cut in shortening.
Mix together egg (slightly beaten), milk and Tabasco sauce.
Add egg mixture to dry ingredients and mix well.
Coat evenly each wiener with batter.
Fry in deep fat until golden brown.
Drain and insert wooden skewer into one end of each wiener.

title: homemade baby wipes
directions: Cut Bounty towels in half so that you have 2 short rolls of towels.
Remove cardboard core with fingers.
Place in container. (I use an empty round wipes container.)
Boil water and add shampoo and lotion; pour over paper towels and replace lid.
These work great and save a lot of money.
You may need to adjust water amount to your liking (I use 3 1/2 cups).

title: sue's ice cream
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl at medium-high speed for 1 minute.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add Eagle Brand, pudding mix and vanilla; beat well.
Stir in 1 quart milk.
Pour into freezer can of 1 gallon freezer.
Add remaining milk.
Freeze according to directions.
Let ripen 1 hour.

title: velvet cake
directions: Put all ingredients in mixing bowl and mix thoroughly.
Add 1 cup boiling water.
Mix.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 60 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured.

title: lemon bars
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, oleo and powdered sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Beat eggs until lemon-colored.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour over crust.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: hot dog sauce
