directions: Brown hamburger and onion together.
Add the rest and simmer until thick.

title: admonition coconut cake
directions: Night before baking cake:
Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut.
Store in refrigerator.

title: shredded potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into casserole dish. Add topping.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: frukt kake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add egg yolks one at a time.
Beat well. Add flour sifted with baking powder alternately with buttermilk. Add remaining ingredients.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter last.
Place in 2 greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add tomato sauce, salt, sugar and garlic. Simmer 20 minutes.
Cook wide noodles according to package directions.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream and green onions.
Place in a greased oblong Pyrex dish, one layer noodles, layer of meat and layer of cheese mixture.
Alternate layers until all ingredients are used.
Grate Cheddar cheese over top.
Bake in a 350° oven about 20 minutes or until bubbly hot.

title: pound cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Icing:
Mix vanilla pudding with cold milk and Dream Whip until smooth.
Refrigerate (or put in freezer to get cold while you make the rest).

title: p.m.s. cake
directions: Bake cake in two round pans (follow instructions on box). Place one layer of cake in a plastic or glass container approximately 6 inches deep.
Using a fork, poke several holes into the cake.
Pour 1/4 cup of Kahlua over the cake.

title: delicious strawberry pie
directions: In a saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over cold water; let stand to soften. Then stir over low heat until gelatin is dissolved. In food processor or blender, puree berries, sugar and gelatin mixture. Pour into a bowl to chill until mixture thickens and mounds, about an hour.

title: pork and egg pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut pork into bite-size pieces; add chopped onion, salt and pepper.
Cover with water.
Simmer 2 hours.
Drain (saving juices).
Line pie plate; add meat and onion.
Sprinkle with herbs.
Lay slices of egg on top.
Thicken juices by mixing with cornstarch and simmering 1 or 2 minutes. Pour over meat and egg in plate.
Cover with pastry, seal edges well and slash middle to let steam escape.
Bake for 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Tie allspice, cloves and cinnamon in cheesecloth to make a spice bag. In a saucepan stir together spice bag, sugar, vinegar and corn syrup. Bring to a boil over medium heat, boil gently 10 minutes. Keep syrup hot. Pack peaches into hot pint jars. Pour boiling syrup into jars, covering peaches, leaving 1/2 inch headspace. With a non metallic utensil remove air bubbles. Wipe rims with damp towel. Seal according to lid manufacturers directions. Process in a boiling water bath for 25 minutes. Cool jars on wire rack or folded towel. Makes about 5 pints.

title: butter pecan cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until well mixed. Beat in eggs.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Blend dry ingredients into creamed mixture.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: sugarless peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream
margarine,
sweetener and peanut butter in bowl. Mix in egg, milk and vanilla.
Sift in flour, salt and baking powder. Mix
well.
Drop
by spoonfuls onto foil-lined cookie sheet. Flatten
with
fork.
Bake
at
for
10 minutes. Cool. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: beef consomme rice
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine and saute onion and green pepper.
Boil beef consomme and mushrooms.
Pour both over dry, uncooked rice in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: roasted vinaigrette potatoes
directions: Place first two ingredients in blender.
Pulse 3 or 4 times. Add the next 5 ingredients and process 20 seconds.
Scrape sides if necessary.
With blender running, pour olive oil in the opening.
Process until well blended.

title: asparagus roll-ups
directions: Trim crusts from bread; flatten slices with rolling pin. Combine softened cheese; spread on bread.
Place one asparagus spear on each slice; roll up.
Place seam side down on baking sheet.
Brush with melted butter.
(This may be prepared this far, covered and frozen until needed, or bake, then freeze.)

title: pancake syrup
directions: Combine sugars, water and corn syrup.
Bring to a boil. Remove from heat and add vanilla and maple flavoring.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough on 14-inch pizza pan and bake according to directions (about 10 to 12 minutes at 375°).
Cook and stir next 4 ingredients over medium heat until mixture coats spoon.
Set aside to cool.
Blend together cream cheese, 1/3 cup sugar, vanilla and milk and spread over cooled cookie crust.
Arrange sliced fruit over cheese layer.
Top with glaze and refrigerate (preferably overnight).
Serve with or without Cool Whip.

title: potato soup
directions: Place the first 6 ingredients in enough of the water (1 to 1 1/2 cups) and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until the vegetables are tender.
Remove from the heat and mash the vegetables.
Add the remaining ingredients, all but milk.
Return to heat and bring to a boil.
Add the evaporated milk.
Turn heat off.
Serves 6.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in brown sugar until dissolved.
Cool these ingredients slightly.
Beat egg and vanilla in well.
Sift, then measure flour.
Resift it with baking powder and salt.
Stir these ingredients into the butter mixture.
Add chopped nuts or coconut.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut into 16 bars.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into uncooked pie shell and bake for 35 minutes at 300°.

title: soft pretzels(healthful eating)
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; add salt, sugar and flour.
Knead 5 to 10 minutes.
Add more flour as necessary to reduce stickiness. Twist dough into shape of cars, trucks, airplanes, animals, flowers, trees, gingerbread boys, numerals or circles.
Place on Teflon baking sheet.
Brush with beaten egg.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: congo bars
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 X 13 pan or spread onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 for 25 minutes.
Cookies will not look done, but don't cook any longer.
They get firm as they cool.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Cut cauliflower and broccoli into bite-sized pieces.
Chop onion and put all into large salad bowl with a cover.
Pour Ranch dressing over the salad.
Cover with top and shake.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Bring directly out of refrigerator - that's it!
Delicious!

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and jam (your choice).
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add (alternating) buttermilk, creamed butter, sugar and dry ingredients, then add raisins, nuts and cherries.
Pour into 3 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done in the center.

title: caramel cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs, milk, flour and vanilla.
Bake in a 375° oven for 25 minutes in 2 (8-inch) layer pans.
Use Caramel Frosting.

title: caramel icing
directions: In saucepan, combine brown sugar, butter or margarine, cream and vanilla, stirring constantly.
Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool.
Beat until spreading consistency.
Icing stays moist on cake for several days and does not form a crust like may cooked icings do!

title: fresh peach crisp
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Cut in margarine with two knives or pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse corn meal.
Combine peaches, lemon juice and water.
Spoon into a greased 9-inch square baking dish.
Sprinkle flour mixture over peaches.
Bake covered at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 35 to 45 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: crab and corn bisque
directions: Saute celery, onions and green pepper in Dutch oven.
Add soup and remaining ingredients except crabmeat and optional ingredients and cook until thoroughly heated.
Gently stir in crabmeat and heat thoroughly.
Remove and discard bay leaves.
Garnish with parsley and lemon slices if desired.
Yield:
11 cups.

title: honeyed apricot biscotti(italian cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly coat cookie sheet with spray; dust with flour.
In a small bowl, whisk together egg whites and honey; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, anise, baking powder, soda and salt.
Make a well in center and pour in egg white mixture and apricots.
Mix until smooth and well combined (about 1 minute). Transfer dough to lightly floured work surface.
Divide in half. Shape each portion into a 12 x 2-inch log.

Arrange logs on baking sheet about 6-inches apart. Bake until logs are golden brown (about 40 minutes). Reduce heat to 300°. Transfer logs to work surface and cool about 3 to 4 minutes. Use a serrated knife and slice each log diagonally into 1/2-inch thick slices.
On baking sheet, arrange slices upright and slightly apart. Bake 15 to 20 minutes more until crisp.
Cool completely. Store in airtight container. Will keep fresh up to 3 weeks.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Warm hot milk and butter together.
Combine salmon (flaked), eggs, seasonings and milk; mix.
Add warm milk and butter; mix. Put in loaf and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: caramel dip for apples
directions: Cream first three ingredients well and add Bits 'O Brickle and vanilla.
Let this sit overnight in refrigerator.
Keeps for several days.

title: sauerkraut and kielbasa
directions: Thoroughly wash and drain sauerkraut.
Saute bacon to crisp. Remove bacon and crumble.
Add onions to skillet and saute in bacon fat until transparent.
Remove onions.
Add sauerkraut to skillet; cover and simmer in bacon fat for approximately 3/4 hour or until tender.
Add water if needed.
Add bacon, onions and brown sugar to kraut.
Heat through.
Parboil kielbasa in water for approximately 15 minutes.
Slice kielbasa and add to kraut.
Serve.

title: half-baked potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes leaving skins on.
On cookie sheet, melt butter or margarine to lightly cover pan bottom.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Place face down on pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
A filled pan will seve 5 to 6.
This is a good way to use up small potatoes, producing baked potatoes with a French fry face.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Mix together and put in 8-inch square pan.
Let set.
Double for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: ham croquettes
directions: *Reserve 1 cup ground cracker crumbs to roll croquettes in.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well and shape into a ball.
Chill.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown the beef; saute onion and cook the noodles.
Then add it all in a large casserole dish with sauce.
Layer beef, noodles, cheese and pepperoni until all used up.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: williamsburg lemon tea cakes
directions: Blend the first 3 ingredients together and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Beat together the next 5 ingredients and pour over baked layer while hot.
Bake again at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar and cut into small squares when cool.
They freeze well.

title: hamburger-cabbage casserole
directions: Cook rice until tender.
Lightly brown meat, onion, salt, pepper and garlic powder in butter.
Add rice to meat mixture. Spread 1/2 of the cabbage in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover with meat mixture.
Top with remaining cabbage.
Pour soup over the top.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream
butter
and
cream cheese.
Add sugar; mix well. Add 1 egg
at
a
time; beat well.
Add vanilla, almond and 2 cups flour at a time.
Bake
at
325° until done, about 1 plus hour.
Test; done when toothpick comes clean.

title: mediterranean chicken
directions: In large skillet, lightly brown sausage; push to side.
Add chicken; brown.
Drain.
Stir in tomatoes and vegetables; cover and simmer 10 minutes.

title: hamburger roll-ups
directions: Brown ground chuck.
Drain.
Add onion soup mix and cheese. Mix.
Separate crescent roll triangles.
Place spoonful of meat mixture on wide end of triangle.
Cover with two ends of dough and roll up.
Make sure all meat mixture is sealed.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Yield: 24.

title: fruit pudding
directions: Set for 1/2 hour in refrigerator.

title: russian tea mix
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Store in airtight container.
Use 2 heaping teaspoonfuls to 1 cup of boiling water.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix together, form a ball.
Sprinkle with paprika and serve with crackers.

title: leigh's low-fat banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray two 9-inch loaf pans with Pam. Beat yogurt, white and brown sugar until dissolved.
Add spices, salt, vanilla, lemon and eggs.
Mix together.
Mix flour, oats, powder and soda in a small bowl.
Add to yogurt mixture, alternately with pureed bananas.
Don't overbeat.
Fold mashed banana in last.
Pour into loaf pans.
Bake on center rack 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool in pans 20 minutes and then remove.
Cool on cake rack.
Makes about 32 slices, about 90 calories each.

title: chicken crescents
directions: Cream the cheese and 2 tablespoons of oleo together; add next 6 ingredients.
Open crescent rolls.
Press halves together to form square.
Spoon 1/4 cup into rolls.
Pull up corners to center and give a twist.
Melt reserved oleo and brush tops.
Sprinkle on bread crumbs.
Bake in ungreased pan for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°. Makes 8.

title: stove top sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes into 1/2-inch slices.
Melt margarine in large covered skillet over medium heat. Brown potato slices in margarine on both sides until all slices have been browned.
Add brown sugar, water and cinnamon to potatoes.
Turn heat to low and cook until potatoes are fork-tender (10 or 15 minutes).

title: white chocolate cookies
directions: Melt chocolate.
Add peanut butter and then other ingredients. Drop on waxed paper.

title: peanut butter-oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter, milk and cocoa in a heavy saucepan; stir well.
Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil; cook 1 minute.
Stir in peanut butter, oats and vanilla; mix well. Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased waxed paper. Cool thoroughly.
Yield:
4 dozen.

title: french chantilly cocktail
directions: In a large bowl, mix together rice, shrimp, cream, peas and mayonnaise.
Season with salt and pepper.
Taste and correct the seasoning.
Chill covered in refrigerator.

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: Add grits to boiling water and salt.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes until liquid is absorbed.
Add butter, cheeses (cut into small cubes), eggs (slightly beaten) and milk.
Mix until cheeses are melted. Pour or spoon into casserole and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Cover and cook over very low heat about 30 minutes or until rice is tender and milk is absorbed.
Stir mix occasionally while cooking. Combine remaining ingredients in a small bowl.
Gradually, stir about 1/4 of hot rice mixture into yolk mixture in small bowl; empty bowl contents into saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat. Serve warm or cold.

title: no fry chicken fingers
directions: Place noodles in container of an electric blender or food processor; process until crumbs form.
Place in a shallow dish and set aside.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Chop garlic fine; crumble cheese in small chunks.
On medium, beat in mixing bowl.
Pour in other ingredients.
Beat for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 1/2 gallons.

title: american chop suey
directions: Saute onion in butter for 3 minutes over medium heat.
Add hamburg and cook completely.
Add garlic, salt, pepper, sugar, sweet basil, parsley and oregano to hamburger.
Add tomato paste and cut up tomatoes (do not drain).
Let simmer 20 minutes to 1/2 hour, uncovered.
Drain cooked macaroni.
Add 2 tablespoons of butter.
Add the mix and 2 cups of tomato juice.

title: cucumber circles
directions: Peel cucumbers. Cut cucumbers into circles. Add vinegar to cucumbers. Add salt and pepper to cucumber and vinegar mix. Let cucumbers set in refrigerator for at least 15 minutes.

title: coconut-cornflake cookies
directions: Cream Crisco.
Add sugars and beat until creamy.
Add eggs and beat.
Add vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Add rest of ingredients, 1 by 1.
Shape into walnut size balls.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.
Cool before removing from cookie sheet.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Sprinkle dry cake mix over pumpkin mixture and sprinkle nuts over cake mix.
Drizzle margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: old south salad dressing
directions: Beat the egg white until fluffy, slowly add 1/2 cup Wesson oil, 1/2 teaspoon salt and garlic powder.
Blend in cornstarch paste, add pimento and Blue cheese.

title: lemon shortbread
directions: Mix as for pie crust.
Press firmly into an 8-inch square pan. Bake 15 to 20 minutes in a 350° oven until firm and light golden brown.

title: fish frying batter
directions: Beat with a wire whisk until smooth.
Dip fish fillets in batter, then in Progresso Italian bread crumbs, coating both sides.
Fry fillets in hot oil until golden brown and fillets are cooked.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Add all ingredients to beaten eggs.
Bake 55 minutes at 325°.

title: fiesta(for a big crowd)
directions: Simmer first six ingredients for one hour.
Layer remaining ingredients.

title: cracker salad
directions: Boil eggs and chop.
Break up crackers.
Add relish and mayonnaise to moisten.
Leftover cornbread, crumbled and browned, may be used in place of the crackers.
Very good!

title: cheese balls
directions: Let cheeses sit out until they reach room temperature.
Mix with potato masher.
Add sauces and mix well.
Add part of the pecans and parsley flakes (about 1/2 cup of each).
Mix and form into balls (1 large or 2 small).
Roll ball in remaining nuts and parsley flakes.

title: tamale rarebit
directions: Melt butter in double boiler.
Add green pepper; cook until tender.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Combine corn and egg. Add to cheese mixture.
Add remaining ingredients except toast; heat thoroughly, stirring constantly.
Serve over hot toast. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: tang fruit dressing or dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: fruit compote
directions: Arrange fruit with juice and liquid from cans.
Add rum.
Bake covered at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: island delight
directions: Mix together butter, 2 c. sifted flour and 1 c. light brown sugar.
Spread evenly in jellyroll pan and bake for 12 minutes at 350.
Cool.
Mix remaining ingredients, except powdered sugar and pour on cooled crust.
Bake at 325 degrees for 25 minutes or until slightly set.
Do not overbake.
Cool thoroughly.
When totally cool, sprinkle powdered sugar on top and cut into small squares.

title: green beans almondine
directions: Brown almonds in bacon drippings and set aside.
Saute onion and add beans, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Refrigerate 6 to 8 hours.

title: poultry seasoning for barbecue chicken
directions: Blend in blender.
Use as a sauce for grilling chicken.

title: marinated broccoli
directions: Mix packet of dressing as directed on envelope.
Peel stalks and break off flowerets.
Slice stalks lengthwise and cut stalks and flowerets into bite size pieces.
About 1 to 1 1/2 hours before serving, pour marinade over the broccoli.

title: peanut butter cereal cookies
directions: Bring Karo syrup and sugar to a boil.
Add chunky peanut butter and coconut.
In large bowl, put Special K cereal; add first mixture.
Form into balls.
Put on wax paper.
Makes 60 cookies.
(Kids love these.)

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, beating well.
Sift flour, measure and sift 3 times again with baking powder and salt.
Add dry mixture alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Divide batter in half.
With one part, cook two light-colored layers.
To the other half of the batter, add raisins, pecans, cloves and cinnamon. Using this batter, bake two more layers.
It is optional to use white or yellow cake mix.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix Stove Top chicken flavor according to directions, set aside.
Mix rice, soup, chestnuts, onion, chicken and seasoning in medium size bowl.
Spray 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam.
Pour mixture into pan.
Top with drained green beans and prepared chicken flavor.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sea island tuna salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together with 1/2 cup Miracle Whip and 1/2 cup sour cream.

title: oven baked lemony sesame chicken
directions: In large bowl, combine lemon juice, brown sugar, oil, salt, ginger and mustard.
Add chicken, toss until coated, cover and refrigerate several hours to marinate.
Turn pieces occasionally.

title: monkey bread i
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in a saucepan on medium heat until margarine melts. Remove from stove and cool, then add the yeast and enough all-purpose flour for a soft dough (approximately 2 1/2 cups). Let rise until doubled. Punch down and roll out to about 1/4-inch thick. Cut in strips about 2 x 3-inches. Melt 1 stick margarine. Dip pieces in margarine and place in Bundt cake pan. Let rise again, then bake. Temperature: 350°. Time: 30 minutes.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and pepper; drain.
Mix beans with barbecue sauce.
Add beef and simmer for 45 minutes.

title: french toast
directions: You also need dish for soaking bread, wire whisk or fork, griddle or Teflon frying pan, no-stick cooking spray and spatula.

title: diabetic apple jelly
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/2 cup of the apple juice.
Bring remaining 1 1/2 cups of juice to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add softened gelatin, stirring to dissolve.
Add liquid sweetener, lemon juice and food coloring as desired.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Ladle into clean half-pint jars; seal.
Keep in refrigerator.
Makes 2 half-pint jars.

title: spiced nuts
directions: *You can use any combo of nuts to total 4 1/2 cups.

title: crab spread
directions: Spread softened cream cheese into circle on serving plate. Spread crabmeat on top of cream cheese.
Spread shrimp sauce on top of cream cheese.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in 9 x 13 baking dish.
Mix soup, dressing, and cranberry sauce in bowl.
Pour over chicken.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: turkey crepes
directions: In a saucepan heat milk and butter until butter melts.
Cool, then add eggs.
Cook crepes in a greased skillet.
Makes 18.

title: red beans and rice with sausage
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat; saute celery, onion and green pepper until soft, about 5 minutes.
Stir in beans, sausage, broth, water and seasonings.
Bring to a boil and stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat; let stand for five minutes.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: sole saute amandine
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper in shallow dish. Dip fish into mixture, coating it on all sides.
In hot oil, in skillet, saute fish over medium heat until golden on both sides and easily flaked with fork.
Remove from pan to warm serving dish.
Melt butter in same skillet, mixing with crusty bits.
Add almonds and lemon juice; cook and stir until brown.
Pour over fish. Sprinkle with parsley. Serve immediately.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: frozen cucumber pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt over sliced cucumbers and onions. Let stand 2 hours. Then, drain off liquid.
Combine sugar and vinegar and pour over pickles.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Stir.
Then place pickles into freezer containers.
Freeze.
Keep frozen at least 2 days before eating.
Thaw container at room temperature.
Then keep refrigerated.
Pickles will keep well in the freezer for one year.

title: banana-strawberry parfait
directions: In a food processor or blender, combine the bananas, brown sugar, lime juice, tequila, cinnamon and cloves. Puree until smooth.
In 6 parfait glasses or glass dessert dishes, layer berries with banana puree.
Cover and refrigerate until slightly chilled before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: walnut meatballs and gravy
directions: Mix beef, walnuts, breadcrumbs, milk, eggs and salt.
Mix well.
Form meatballs; brown in skillet.
Mix soup mix with boiling water.
Pour over meatballs in baking dish.
Add more water if needed to cover completely.
Place in oven at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: * five cup salad *
directions: Fold all ingredients together and refrigerate to blend flavors.

title: pinto beans and ham
directions: Soak pinto beans overnight.
Rinse and add cold water with ham bone.
Let cook until done.
Slowly add remaining ingredients and cook additional 30 minutes.

title: mexicali rice
directions: In large pot, brown beef until tender.
Add onion and green peppers.
Cook until tender.
Drain fat.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Bring to a boil with pot uncovered.
Cover and simmer on low heat for 35 minutes, stirring once in a while, until rice is done.

title: creole seasoning
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in an airtight container in a cool place.
Yields 1/3 cup.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Slice chicken thin.
Mix bread crumbs and cheese together with salt and pepper to taste.
Dip sliced chicken into egg mixture, then press into bread crumbs.
Let set 15 minutes.
Heat oil and butter mixture until foamy, then add chicken and cook 2 to 3 minutes or until lightly browned.
Add wine and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Turn occasionally to ensure this won't dry out too much. If needed, add more wine.
Yields 4 servings.

title: cheese grits casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 2-quart casserole dish.
Stir in cheese, butter, nutmeg, salt, peppers and garlic into hot grits.
Beat eggs; mix into grits.
Pour into dish.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Dip chicken in water; shake off excess water.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Coat chicken on all sides with 1/2 cup flour.
Place on wire rack and let dry 15 minutes.
Pour oil in skillet to reach 1/2-inch deep.
Heat over medium heat until hot enough to sizzle a drop of water.
Add chicken, skin side down.
Cook 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to low and cook 20 minutes longer.
Turn chicken pieces over and cook until chicken is tender, 15 to 20 minutes longer.

title: butter pound cake
directions: Cream
butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add baking powder, vanilla and salt; add flour and milk alternately.
Bake in floured tube pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 45 minutes longer.
(For chocolate pound cake, add 1/2 cup cocoa.) Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: mimosa
directions: Divide orange juice and liqueur evenly into 4 wine glasses. Fill slowly with champagne.

title: sukiyaki
directions: Cut vegetables into 2 or 3-inch pieces.
Cut tofu into 8-12 pieces.
Set vegetables, tofu beef and noodles on a large platter. Mix sauce A (see below) and sauce B (see below).

title: strawberry punch(or any flavor you like)
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 4 cups of water.
Mix sugar and 9 cups of water.
Add pineapple juice.
Mix all ingredients.
Freeze in 4 milk cartons (paper) for 2 days.
Can be kept frozen longer.
Let thaw 2 hours before needed.
Add 2 bottles of ginger ale to each half gallon of punch.
Serves 40 people.

title: vegetable barley soup
directions: In 4-quart saucepan brown meat.
Add onion and garlic, cook until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients except frozen vegetables.
Bring to boil after covering.
Reduce heat, simmer 50 to 60 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add frozen vegetables. Cook about 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Additional water may be added if needed.

title: carrot soup extraordinaire
directions: Saute onion in butter. Add carrots and chicken stock.
Simmer until carrots are tender.
Puree in blender.
Add orange juice concentrate and cream.
Add 2 or 3 dashes of powdered cloves. Wonderful served hot or cold.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: spicy cabbage soup
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add other ingredients and cook 45 minutes.
I used Campbell's beef bouillon (canned soup) for one-half of the beef soup.
I also added a little "Joe's Stuff," a spice from New Orleans.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Grind peppers, tomatoes, and onions with food chopper and drain in colander.
Add peppers, tomatoes, onions, mustard and vinegar. Bring to a boil.
Let cook 10 minutes, then add flour, sugar and salt.
Let boil 10 minutes more.
Let cool, then add mayonnaise. Put into jars and seal.

title: waverly chicken casserole
directions: Line pan with Waverly Wafer cracker crumbs.
Add layer of sliced water chestnuts, a layer of cooked chicken breasts.
Mix the chicken soup, mushroom soup and sour cream and pour over chicken. Cover with Waverly Wafer crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Over low heat and stirring until mixed, combine apricot preserves and Italian dressing in a saucepan.
Arrange chicken in baking dish and pour sauce over it.
Bake at 350° until chicken is cooked, about 30 to 45 minutes.
If desired, place dried apricots on top of chicken half way through cooking time so they plump up before serving.

title: zesty grilled seafood
directions: Pour all of the ingredients over the fish and marinate for 30 minutes.
Broil for 8 minutes on each side.
Serves 4.

title: layered italian casserole
directions: Brown beef,
onions
and
garlic in skillet. Drain fat. Stir in tomato
sauce,
parsley,
salt
and
oregano.
In
8 x 12-inch shallow
baking dish, layer the spaghetti, meat sauce, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese. Top with Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 5 servings.

title: apple scripture cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Add eggs and other ingredients, one at a time.
Mix well.
Bake in 2 or 3 greased and floured loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar to mixture and then add eggs.
Mix together.
Add baking powder, soda, spices and salt to flour.
Mix good.
Then add to sugar mixture.
Drop by teaspoon on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Cool.

title: holiday ham glaze
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Glaze ham with this mixture every 15 minutes for the last hour of baking.

title: curry chicken cheese ball
directions: Mix well.
Roll into ball and chill.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla, then add Cool Whip.
Put on cooked base and arrange fruits.
Mix vanilla and apple jelly and brush on top of fruits.
Sprinkle on coconut.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: cranberry apple dish
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; put in a large casserole dish. Mix the nuts, butter, brown sugar and flour; sprinkle over top of apple-cranberry mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: cheese cake
directions: Cream milk and cream cheese together with mixer.
Add lemon juice; mix well.
Pour into crust.
Chill.
May be topped with any fruit pie filling.

title: oatmeal crisp cookies
directions: Combine the butter, sugar and eggs.
Sift together the flour, salt and baking powder.
Add alternately the milk.
Fold in the raisins, figs, almonds or pecans, honey and spice to taste.
See Proverbs 23:14 and beat well.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in moderate oven at 375° for 30 minutes, then at 300°.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix together;
pour
into an 8-inch pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
(Add 1/2 cup nuts, optional.)

title: diabetic cream of mushroom soup
directions: Simmer mushrooms in broth 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 15 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Destem mushrooms. Mix cooked, crumbled bacon, cream cheese and seasoned salt together. Stuff mixture in mushrooms and place in dish. Melt the butter and pour in on top of stuffed mushrooms. Bake at 400° until cheese is melted.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine the flour and baking soda and set aside.
Using an electric mixer on low speed, combine the brown sugar and oil.
Add egg, water and vanilla and beat until smooth.
Add flour mixture in 3 parts at low speed.
Scrape bowl well after each addition. Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls onto baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool on baking sheets for 1 minute.
Remove to cooling rack.
Contains per serving: 80 calories; 2 grams fat; 60 mg. sodium and 10 mg. cholesterol.

title: copper penny salad
directions: Mix the last 6 ingredients.
Boil mix and add to vegetables. Let set in refrigerator overnight for best flavor.
Will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: creamed pepper casserole
directions: Boil peppers in salted water 10 minutes; drain.
Mix with soup, grated cheese and salt and pepper to taste.
Crumble cracker crumbs over top; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Put in a baking dish.
Crush 1 stick Ritz crackers and mix with 1 stick melted oleo.
Sprinkle crumbs on top of vegetable mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cornish hens
directions: Thaw hens.
Follow directions on package for stuffing mix. Spoon stuffing into cavity of each hen.
Mix butter with sugar, lime juice, wine and soy sauce.
Brush hens with sauce.
Place on rack or trivet in slow cooking pot.
For 3 1/2 quart pot, place hens on end, neck end down.
Cover and cook on low 5 to 7 hours. Baste at least once during cooking, if possible.

title: fix and forget dinner
directions: Mix all ingredients and turn into a buttered casserole.
Do not brown meat first.
Cover and bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Serve with flaky garlic rounds.

title: green bean-pork casserole(low-fat)
directions: Cut into pieces and saute the onion and mushrooms in a lightly sprayed skillet. Add pork or chicken and brown.
Dilute the cream soup with water or milk and pour into skillet. Cover and cook for 5 to 10 minutes.
Line casserole dish with green beans. Add meat and pour soup over top. Cover and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
(Contains around 10 fat grams for pork or 7 for chicken.)

title: pina colada ice cream cake roll(makes 10 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to moderate (375°).
Grease 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan; line with wax paper.
Grease paper.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt onto second piece of wax paper.
Beat eggs in bowl until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sugar until very thick, 5 minutes. Stir in vanilla and water.
Gently fold in flour mixture.
Spread batter in pan.
Bake in preheated moderate oven (375°) for 12 minutes or until center springs back when lightly pressed with fingertip.
Loosen cake around edges with small spatula.
Invert onto clean towel dusted with 10x sugar; peel off wax paper.
Roll up cake and towel together from short end.
Cool completely on wire rack.

title: caramel corn
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in 2-quart pan.
Bring to boil. Stir constantly for 5 minutes.
Do not over cook.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla; stir.
Add soda; stir.
Pour over popcorn and mix until all kernels are covered.
Spread on cookie sheets.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: pizza bake
directions: Brown meat, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Mix in sauces.
Stir and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Add mushrooms and pepperoni.
Layer and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: heather's cookies
directions: Mix in pan the sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Put on medium heat and cook until it starts to boil.
Cool for 1 minute. Add vanilla, salt, peanut butter and oatmeal; mix well.
Drop by spoonful onto wax paper.

title: wacky cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients together and pour batter into a buttered 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons dressing in large skillet on medium-high heat.
Add chicken and garlic powder.
Stir-fry 3 minutes.
Add vegetables; stir-fry 3 minutes until chicken is cooked through. Reduce heat to medium.
Stir in remaining dressing and soy sauce; simmer 1 minute.
Serve over hot cooked rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: *Can be cut in half or left whole.

title: caramel monkey bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In small saucepan, melt margarine.
Coat bottom and sides of ungreased 12-cup fluted tube pan with 2 tablespoons melted margarine.
Sprinkle 3 tablespoons nuts over bottom of prepared pan.
Add remaining nuts, brown sugar and water to remaining margarine; heat to boiling, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat.
Separate dough into 20 biscuits; cut each biscuit into quarters.
Place half the quarters in bottom of prepared pan.
Drizzle half of the caramel sauce over biscuits. Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Invert immediately onto waxed paper and remove from pan.

title: easy gumbo
directions: Saute sausage until lightly browned.
Combine with remaining ingredients and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Serve over cooked rice.
Freezes well.

title: turkish onion salad
directions: Arrange mandarin slices on lettuce leaves alternately with red onions.
Top with black olives.
Combine olive oil and lemon juice, salt and pepper to taste, pour over salad.
Serves 4.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour hot water over oatmeal and let stand.
Cream brown sugar, white sugar and shortening, then beat eggs into mixture.
Sift flour (cake or self-rising), cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to shortening mixture, then add oatmeal mixture.
Stir all together well and bake at 350° for 35 minutes in an oblong cake pan.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine all vegetables mixing well.
Combine remaining ingredients mixing well and pour over vegetables.
Chill for 24 hours.
Drain before serving.

title: pound cake
directions: Allow butter and Crisco to soften at room temperature.
Blend in.
Add sugar and eggs.
Add 2 cups flour with 1/2 cup milk and blend in, adding remaining flour and milk.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: "chicken pie"
directions: Place chicken pieces in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix soup and stock in saucepan.
Heat over medium burner to boiling point, stirring.
Pour over chicken.
Mix flour, salt, milk and margarine and
pour	over
above.
Bake
for 1/2 hour or until brown,
in a 425° oven, basting with any remaining stock a few times.

title: butter rich crescent rolls
directions: Scald milk and cool.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, salt, butter and egg.
Stir in flour to form soft dough.
Knead 3 to 4 minutes.
Put into a greased bowl; cover and let rise again until double.
Punch down, shape and let rise until double again. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: amaretto mustard glaze
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and boil gently, uncovered, until reduced to 1 cup, about 8 minutes.
Cool.
Brush on ham, turkey, chicken or duck during the last 30 minutes of cooking time.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add eggs, bananas, oats and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.

title: coconut pie filling for fried pies
directions: Mix flour, sugar and water well.
Cook over very low heat until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, food coloring, vanilla, coconut flavoring and coconut.
Mix well.
Cool.
It's ready for pies to be made.

title: hungarian fruit squares
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in margarine with pastry blender. Beat eggs and vanilla together.
Blend together.
Roll into ball and put 1/4 aside.
Press dough into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: bacon and tomato potato skins
directions: Clean and poke potatoes with a fork; cook on High in microwave 17 to 22 minutes or until almost tender.
Rearrange once.
Halve each potato lengthwise.
Scoop out the inside of each half, leaving about 1/4-inch thick shell.
Cover and chill the leftovers.
Combine the oil, chili powder and pepper.
Brush the inside with oil mixture.
Cut the potato halves lengthwise; sprinkle with bacon, tomato and onion.
Top with cheese.
Bake in a 450° oven for 10 to 12 minutes until cheese melts.
Serve with sour cream.

title: healthy gummy chews
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine 1 cup juice with the gelatin powder. Bring 1 cup of juice to a boil, then stir in gelatin mix.
Add remaining juice and stir until gelatin is dissolved.

title: doggie on a stick
directions: Mix
egg and milk.
Add dry ingredients.
Place hot dog on stick and dip in batter.
Place end with hot dog on it into deep fry for 1 1/2 minutes at 375°.
Children just love these.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Brown the butter in the soup kettle (don't burn).
Add the potatoes, covering with enough water to go over them 1 inch.
Add salt.
Bring to boil and continue until potatoes are soft.
Add milk and Cheddar cheese soup.
Stir often, making sure this doesn't boil hard.

title: date squares
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking soda and salt; add brown sugar and rolled oats and mix well.
Cut butter into flour mixture until well blended.
Press one half of butter mixture on sides and bottom of greased 9-inch square pan.
Cover with date mixture and sprinkle remaining butter mixture on top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven about 30 minutes.
When cool, cut into squares and remove from pan.
Yields 25 squares.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Drain vegetables, mix together and set aside.
Mix salad oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper together.
Heat to boiling; pour over vegetables.
Let set overnight or at least 8 hours.
This will keep for several weeks.

title: cheesy vegetables
directions: *Any combination of broccoli, cauliflower, carrots or celery.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes in oven or microwave until done.
Cut potatoes in half.
Scoop out insides of potatoes.
Into large bowl, combine all other ingredients, reserving 1 cup of cheese; use spoon to put filling back in potato shells.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake in 400° oven until cheese is melted, about 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: red onion-topped potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Bake potatoes about 1 hour or until tender. Cut potatoes lengthwise in half.
Score tops crisscross fashion, being careful not to cut through skin.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: seafood phyllo triangles
directions: Combine shrimp or crab meat, cream cheese, scallions, garlic, Tabasco and Worcestershire sauce in bowl.
Taste and adjust seasoning, if necessary.
It should be strongly flavored.
To assemble, place a sheet of phyllo dough on work surface and brush with butter.
Layer another sheet and repeat.
Cut dough into 6 strips.
Place 1 to 2 heaping teaspoons of cheese mixture onto each strip.
Fold like a flag into a triangle shape.
Lightly butter tops.
Repeat until dough and filling are used up.
Bake in preheated 400° oven 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: In a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, put rice.
Sprinkle dry onion soup over rice.
Add 2 cups of water.
Layer raw chicken pieces over mixture.
Add drained mushrooms.
Combine the soups; spread over chicken.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove cover; bake for 15 minutes.

title: strawberry delight salad
directions: Combine pretzels and margarine; press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: pasta and cheese
directions: Brown ground beef in large frying pan; add onion and garlic and cook until onions are limp.
Add spaghetti sauce, tomatoes, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Cook 1 pound macaroni.
Put 1/2 in casserole; spread meat mixture over top, then a layer of sour cream over that and then thin Provolone cheese slices.
Add rest of macaroni, meat, sour cream and Mozzarella slices on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove cover towards end of baking time to melt and brown cheese. Double recipe to make 2 casseroles and freeze one.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix well above ingredients in large container.
Use 2 full teaspoons to make one cup of hot tea.
Adjust amount for individual taste.

title: potato bread
directions: Boil or bake potatoes; mash well.
Add butter, sugar, flour, extract and salt.
Mix well and bake in loaf or balls on cookie sheet in moderate oven about 20 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Add red jello prepared with 1/2 amount of liquid as stated. Add crushed pineapple, nuts, grapes and celery (optional).

title: hot chocolate
directions: Combine chocolate, sugar, and 1/4 cup milk in medium saucepan over medium-low heat.
Cook, stirring constantly until chocolate melts.
Add remaining 3 3/4 cups milk; heat until hot, stirring occasionally.
Do Not Boil!
Stir in vanilla.

title: italian peas
directions: Place all ingredients in 1/2 cup water.
Cook 40 minutes on medium heat.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and Crisco until fluffy.
Add egg yolks.
Sift flour and soda; add alternately with buttermilk, ending with dry ingredients.
Add vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in three 9-inch pans for approximately 25 minutes at 350°.

title: summer squash medley
directions: Boil squash and onions in salted water for 5 to 10 minutes. Drain and set aside.
Combine soup, sour cream and carrots.
Fold in squash; set aside.
Mix margarine and stuffing.
Put 1/2 stuffing mixture on top of squash.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Can be made ahead and baked later.

title: cheese crunchies
directions: Cream cheese and butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop from spoon to make small bite-size pieces of dough.
Bake 18 minutes at 375°.

title: candlelight salad
directions: Rinse and drain lettuce leaf.
Place on salad plate.
Place pineapple slice on lettuce leaf.
Cut banana flat on bottom to stand straight. Stand banana upright in pineapple hole.
Place cherry on top of banana to make the flame, using toothpicks to keep it in place.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Sprinkle in rice; add chicken, onion and salt.
Spoon soup over chicken; pour broth over.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.
You may sprinkle paprika on top if desired.
tags: cream of chicken and mushroom soup

title: shrimp or chicken jambalaya
directions: Melt butter in wok and add onions, garlic and peppers.
Saute. Add everything, except meat or shrimp.
Place chicken or shrimp in about 15 or 20 minutes before done.
Gradually add water; stir often.
It should be done when rice is tender.

title: peanut butter chocolate bars
directions: Melt margarine.
Add cracker crumbs, peanut butter and confectioners sugar; mix well.
Spread in a 9 x 12-inch pan. Press well.
Melt chocolate bits and butter.
Spread over crumb mixture.
Refrigerate until chocolate sets.
Very good!

title: company chicken
directions: Put chicken in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Place whole mushrooms around chicken.
Mix soup, sour cream and sherry.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with toasted almonds.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Set aside.
Heat broth and other ingredients and simmer for 5 minutes.
Put chicken and broth in casserole and cover with crushed corn flakes.
Bake for 35 minutes at 375°.

title: oreo delight
directions: Crush oreos, setting 1 cup aside for topping. Spread remaining cookies in 9 x 13 inch pan. Pour melted margarine on top and place in refrigerator for 1 hour. Beat cream cheese and sugar, add one carton Cool Whip. Spread over cookie mixture and chill for 1 hour. Mix pudding according to package directions. Pour pudding on top of cookie mixture, refrigerate. Spread remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle with reserved crushed cookies before serving.

title: hot apple punch
directions: Combine ingredients in large stock pot.
Bring to a boil. Simmer 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: daddy's fried green tomatoes
directions: Fry bacon and
remove
from grease.
Saute onions until tender and
remove
from
grease.
Brown
tomatoes
lightly. Combine all ingredients and cover and cook over low heat for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sprinkle sugar over apples.
Stir together and add to apples the flour, soda and cinnamon.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir only until well mixed.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: tuna vegetable pilaf
directions: In heavy, 1 1/2-quart saucepan (with tight lid), combine rice, chicken stock, water, lemon juice, dill, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir in vegetables.
Cover; continue cooking 5 more minutes, until liquid is absorbed.
Blend in sour cream and tuna. Serve hot or cold.

title: pennsylvania dutch salad dressing
directions: Chop bacon and fry until crisp.
Add all other ingredients to beaten egg and pour into fried bacon.
Cook until thickened.
Pour hot over shredded cabbage or lettuce or potatoes.
Makes approximately 1 quart.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour hot water over oatmeal.
Let stand while preparing cake mixture.
Cream together butter, sugars and eggs.
Add cinnamon and baking soda.
Mix well.
Add flour, salt and oatmeal.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat; drain off oil.
Add onion, cooking until clear. In a separate saucepan, combine tomato sauce and cheeses.
Bring to slow boil, stirring constantly.
Pour chips on individual plate and scoop desired amount of meat and sauce.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken in pan.
Cover with cheese.
Add milk to soup; stir and pour over chicken and cheese. Sprinkle with bread crumbs and top with melted margarine.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: gingerbread
directions: Sift flour once; measure.
Add baking powder, soda, salt and spices.
Cream shortening; add sugar gradually.
Cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Combine water and molasses.
Add dry mixture to creamed mixture alternately with liquid mixture until smooth after each addition.
Bake in a greased pan, 10 x 10 x 2-inch, in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and press to 1/2-inch thickness on cookie sheet.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into squares and roll in flour.
Fry in butter; place in a casserole dish.
Add soup and 1 soup can of water to drippings in pan.
Mix well and pour over meat in casserole.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: jam thumbprints
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding flour last.
Shape into balls. Place on cookie sheet.
Make indentation atop each ball with your thumb.
Fill hole with jam.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 13 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Mix the 1 cup cornstarch, eggs, salt and pepper. Add enough milk to make a batter of medium consistency.
Stir lightly. Coat pork cubes in batter and deep fry in hot oil until done. Set aside.

title: artichoke hot dip
directions: Mix together and put in a baking dish; sprinkle well with paprika and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with chips.

title: quick and good lasagna
directions: Brown beef and drain off fat.
Add spaghetti sauce mix, tomato sauce and tomato paste.
Rinse cans and add 2 cans water.
Add Parmesan cheese.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Cook and drain lasagna noodles.

title: lazy daisy cake
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar and beat 2 minutes.
Add dry ingredients, sifted together.
Bring milk to boiling point; add butter and vanilla to milk.
Cool slightly, then add to batter. Batter will be thin.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done. Remove from oven and immediately spread with Coconut Topping.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and 3 tablespoons butter in saucepan on low. Cool.
Blend in remaining butter with cream cheese.
Add until soft.
Add 1/4 cup sugar beating well.
Blend in egg, 1 tablespoon flour, 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and set aside.
Beat 2 eggs until light; add 3/4 cup sugar adding next 6 ingredients one at a time and blend this mixture into the chocolate.
Spread 1/2 of chocolate batter on greased 8-inch square pan.
Add cheese mix spreading evenly, then top with tablespoons of remaining chocolate batter and zigzag spatula to marble.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool and cut bars.

title: hunter's casserole
directions: Just dump all the ingredients together in a casserole dish and bake at 325° for about 2 1/2 hours.
(Meat will be very tender.) Serve over rice.

title: recipe for a happy child
directions: Boil together with care, security, love, religion, kindness, safety and loving parents.
Keep hot at all times.
Never let get warm.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake forever.

title: chicken pot pie ii
directions: De-bone chicken and cut into smaller pieces or use canned chicken.
Mix all ingredients together in a medium pot and bring to a boil.
Place 2 pie crusts on a foil-lined large cookie sheet and pour mixture into crusts, dividing amounts evenly.
Top with remaining pie crusts.
Cut a slit at the top of each crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until tops are brown.
Leftovers heat up well in microwave!

title: garlic rolls
directions: Cut rolls
in
half
and
scoop out some of the center. Mix remaining ingredients as filling.
Fill rolls with cheese mixture. Wrap
rolls
individually in foil.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Rolls may be frozen and reheated.

title: peaches alessandra
directions: Clean and rinse the strawberries, put them in a blender with the sugar.
Blend to obtain a sauce.
Drain the peaches and cut them in thin slices.
To serve, place the sliced peaches in 4 bowls, add the ice cream in the center and pour the strawberry sauce on the ice cream and peaches.

title: pepperoni and broccoli salad
directions: Prepare dressing according to package directions and set aside.
Use only broccoli flowerets for salad.
Combine all ingredients and cover with dressing.
Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.

title: crispy spicy oven fried catfish with tartar sauce
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Coat bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with Crisco oil.
Combine cornmeal, pepper, garlic salt, lemon pepper and Cajun spice in large flat dish.
Combine egg and water.
Rinse fish.
Dip in egg mixture.
Coat with cornmeal mixture.
Place in pan.
Bake at 425° for 22 to 25 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with fork.
Serve with tartar sauce if desired. Makes 4 servings.

title: pasinda-e-khaas
directions: Cut meat into very thin pasinda-style slices.
Wash and drain well. Fry onions in oil until golden. Drain on paper towels; let cool then crush with the back of a spoon.
Set aside.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Combine popcorn and pecans in lightly greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Mix well; set aside.
Melt butter; add brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Boil 5 minutes without stirring. Remove from heat.
Stir in soda and vanilla.
Pour syrup over corn, stirring to coat corn and nuts.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, stirring after 15 minutes.
Cool completely and break apart.
Store in airtight container.

title: german skillet dinner
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter.
Layer sauerkraut, rice, then onion and green pepper.
Top with hamburger, salt and pepper, then place tomatoes on top of that.
Do not stir.
Cook, covered, over low heat for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve from skillet.

title: squash croquettes
directions: Cook squash in a small amount of water until tender; drain and mash.
Add 2 cups bread crumbs and next 5 ingredients.
Add more bread crumbs if mixture is too soft.
Shape into 18 logs; roll each in cornmeal.
Deep fry in hot oil at 375°.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all.
Chill; keep covered until ready to serve.

title: pasta with broccoli
directions: In large saucepan, cook broccoli in boiling unsalted water until tender (2 or 3 minutes).
Rinse under cold water.
Set aside.
In another large saucepan, heat 1 tablespoon olive oil. Lightly brown garlic.
Add parsley, oregano, chicken broth and wine.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Cook pasta of your choice according to package directions.
Drain and place in large heated serving bowl. Add 3 tablespoons olive oil and grated cheese and toss well.
Add broccoli to warmed sauce and toss.
Calories 300 and fat 6 g. Serves 4 to 6.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and water.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix.
Turn into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: 7 layer cookie bars
directions: Mix melted butter and graham cracker crumbs; place in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Place remaining ingredients in pan in order.
After nuts, press ingredients down firmly and then pour milk over all. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: flounder in white wine sauce
directions: Sprinkle both sides of fillet with salt and pepper; arrange in a single layer in a greased baking dish.
Place tomato slices over fillets.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Melt butter in saucepan and blend in flour.
Gradually add milk and cook, stirring constantly until thick and without lumps.
Remove from heat and stir in wine and basil.
Pour sauce over the tomatoes and bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until the fish flakes when tested with a fork.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve.
Serves 6.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Cream the sour cream and cream cheese together; add sugar. Fold in peaches, cherries, pineapple, marshmallows and nuts. Slice to serve.

title: tomato soup
directions: Cook first 2 ingredients with celery seed tied in bag for 1 hour.
Then run through colander.
Add sugar, red pepper and salt. Combine butter and flour.
Add to mixture.
Cook for 20 minutes. Pour in can and seal.
Ready to serve when heated.

title: jambalaya
directions: Brown sausage in heavy skillet.
Remove from drippings.
Add flour to drippings.
Brown flour until dark.
Add onions, parsley and garlic.
Cook until soft, then add water and rice, salt and pepper and sausage.
When it comes to a boil, lower heat to lowest point and cook for about 1 hour, covered tightly.
When rice is done, remove lid and let cook for a few minutes until rice dries a little.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: bon appetit's one bowl apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Combine first 8 ingredients in a large bowl and blend well.
Turn into prepared dish and bake until cake tests done, about 1 hour.

title: caramel coma
directions: Combine crushed cookie crumbs and butter.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, until golden brown.
Set aside to cool.
Place 3 unopened cans of sweetened condensed milk completely submerged in slow boiling water bath (large pan; low heat) for 3 hours.
Do not let water level get below top of cans.
Cool cans; open when cooled.
Spread over crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Chill 1 hour.

title: hawaiian meat balls
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix lightly but thoroughly. Shape meat mixture into 30 balls.
Roll in flour.
Brown meat balls in shortening.
Drain excess fat.

title: classic spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown sausage, onion, green pepper and garlic; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer uncovered 20 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 8 servings.

title: half moon cookies
directions: Cream the sour cream, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well.
In separate bowl, mix flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Ice flat side, half chocolate and half vanilla. Makes 48.

title: nachos
directions: Combine tomatoes and cheese in the top of a doubler boiler. Cook over medium heat until cheese is melted.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients and mix with sweet potatoes.
Mix milk and eggs and combine with potato mixture.
Pour into 9-inch pie pan (deep).
Bake in very hot oven, 450°, for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake for 35 minutes longer.
Use electric mixer to blend ingredients with potato.

title: chicken chunks
directions: Wash and dry chicken breast.
Cut into bite size chunks.
In a shallow bowl, mix flour, salt and pepper. Dredge chicken in flour mixture.
In a small bowl, combine milk and egg. Dunk chicken nuggets in milk-egg mixture, then roll in bread crumbs.
Bake in a preheated 425° oven for 10 to 15 minutes. Serve with catsup, barbecue sauce or sweet and sour sauce.

title: cheese cake dessert
directions: In a small bowl, dissolve jello in hot water.
Set aside. Crush the graham crackers.
Mix with butter and 10x sugar.
Press in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan, saving 4 tablespoons for topping. Cream together the cheese, sugar and vanilla; set aside. Whip the Pet milk and add to jello mixture.
Beat.
Add cream cheese mixture; mix well.
Pour over crumbs and sprinkle with the 4 tablespoons crumbs. Chill.

title: kids' favorite cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions on box; set aside.
Mix the brown sugar, chocolate chips, nuts and flour in separate bowl. Pour 1/2 cake batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle half of dry mix over top.
Add remaining cake batter, then sprinkle remainder of dry mix over top.
Bake according to directions on box.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Combine butter, onion and green pepper.
Microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes.
Mix with shredded potatoes.
Spread mixture evenly in pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes while browning sausage in skillet.
In separate dish, mix eggs, milk, seasoning and 1/2 cup cheese.
Pour 1/2 of mixture over crust. Sprinkle with sausage.
Pour remaining egg mixture over sausage. Top with remaining cheese (and more shredded potatoes, if desired).
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, stirring often.

title: the "late for supper" supper
directions: Brown hamburger; drain off grease.
Over low heat, mix together Velveeta, beef and soups.
Heat until smooth.
(Do not dilute soups.)
Boil noodles until tender and drain.
If onion is desired, dice and brown with hamburger.

title: mediterranean nachos
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cut each pita horizontally in half.
Cut each half into quarters.
Arrange pieces cut-side up on a cookie sheet.
Bake until golden brown, 5 to 6 minutes.
Remove, but keep oven on.
Gently rub tops of pita quarters with garlic cloves taking care not to break pitas.
Arrange them on an ovenproof plate.
In medium bowl, combine tomatoes, Mozzarella, parsley, vinegar, basil, salt and red pepper flakes.
Spoon mixture onto pita pieces.
Bake until cheese melts, about 5 minutes.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Prepare brownie mix, and bake according to package directions in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Let cool and crumble.
Prepare pudding mix according to package directions, omitting chilling.

Place one-third of crumbled brownies in bottom of a 3-quart trifle dish. Top with one-third each of pudding, whipped topping and candy. Repeat layers twice with remaining ingredients, ending with candy. Chill 8 hours.
Yields 16 to 18 servings.

title: apple muffins
directions: Combine brown sugar, pecans, and cinnamon; set aside.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt.
In another bowl, mix together milk, oil, egg, and apples.
Add to dry ingredients (flour, etc.) and stir until everything is just moistened.
Fill paper muffin cups 3/4 full, then top with brown sugar/nut mixture. Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: raisin zucchini bread
directions: Finely shred zucchini; set aside.
Cream the sugar and oil; add eggs, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix well.
Combine flour, cinnamon, salt, baking soda and baking powder; mix well.
Add raisins and walnuts into dry ingredients.
Combine with zucchini mixture; mix well.
Pour into two 9 x 5-inch, greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes, then turn out on wire rack to cool.
Enjoy.

title: seafood paella
directions: Brown chicken in hot oil in a large Dutch oven.
Remove chicken and set aside.
Add onions and garlic.
Saute until tender.
Add tomatoes and 1/2 teaspoon of salt.
Return chicken to Dutch oven. Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in rice, oregano and 1/2 teaspoon of salt.
Dissolve saffron in boiling water.
Pour over chicken and cover.
Simmer 25 minutes.
Saute shrimp in garlic butter until pink (few minutes).
Saute scallops in garlic butter for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Use 10-inch tube pan, greased.

title: cheesy french loaf
directions: Slice bread in 1/2 to 3/4-inch pieces.
Butter each and sprinkle with garlic powder.
Top with cheeses and broil, just until melted.
Serve.

title: sheet cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt in bowl.
In saucepan, bring to boil the shortening, margarine, water and cocoa.
Pour over the flour mixture while still hot.
Add the buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Pour batter into a large greased sheet cake pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chip chopped ham
directions: Mix all together in casserole bowl and bake at 350° for one hour with cover on, then for the last 10 minutes with cover off.

title: crab on crispy english muffin
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Mix crab meat, butter and cheese. Spread on split muffins. Cut into 1/4 wedges. Place quarters on a baking sheet. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly and browned. Serve hot.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in fourths. Mix granulated sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon in pie pan or plastic bag. Roll biscuit quarters in cinnamon/sugar and drop in buttered tube pan. Set aside. Melt margarine and add brown sugar and 2 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon. Mix together and pour this mixture over biscuits in tube pan. Bake for 35 minutes. Turn out of pan while hot. Best served warm. Pull sections right off the loaf.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Pat sugar cookie dough into a pizza pan.
Bake until golden brown.
Set aside to cool.
Mix the Cool Whip, cream cheese and sugar together until well blended.
Spread over sugar cookie dough.
Slice fruit.
Top Cool Whip mixture with fruit slices. Sprinkle powdered sugar over fruit.
Chill and serve.

title: low-fat frozen strawberry delight
directions: Stir whipped topping, yogurt and gelatin in large bowl until smooth.
Stir in cake cubes.
Spoon mixture into 8-inch square pan.
Freeze 3 hours or until firm.
Cut into squares.
Store leftover dessert in freezer.
Makes 12 servings.
Nutrition information per serving:
110 calories, 2.5 gm fat, 0 mg cholesterol, 95 mg sodium, 19 gm carbohydrate, 0 gm dietary fiber, 3 gm protein.

title: pooh-poohs
directions: Fry sausage and ground meat.
Drain and add cheese to meat mixture.
Mix together and spread on cocktail bread.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: english trifle
directions: In the bottom of a pretty, deep glass dish, put the ladyfingers, then pour the sherry over them.
Add the fruit cocktail.
Mix up the Jell-O as directed on the package, then pour over mixture in dish.
Prepare pudding mix as directed.
When Jell-O has set, put pudding on top of Jell-O.
Prepare custard powder (any custard recipe) or Vallergas has custard powder.
When custard thickens, add sliced banana and put this on top of pudding. When this is done, top with fresh whipped cream (any cream will do).
You may finish it off with fresh strawberries on top and colored cake confetti.

title: grape jelly
directions: Remove stems from grapes and crush.
Place in large pan.

Add 1/2 cup water. Bring to a boil and simmer until grapes are fully cooked (stir occasionally). Strain cooked grapes, saving juice. Measure 4 cups of juice. Stir in sugar and add margarine. Bring mixture to a full rolling boil over high heat, stirring constantly.
Quickly stir in fruit pectin and boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Immediately fill scalded jars with hot jelly mixture.
Cover and seal jars.

title: better than canned play dough
directions: Combine and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, for 3 to 5 minutes. The dough will be done when it pulls away from the pan and forms a ball. Remove from pan. Cool slightly and knead. Keeps a long time in an airtight container.
If it dries, have kids dampen hands before playing.

title: clam chowder
directions: Drain clams, save liquid and chop clams.
Fry salt pork or bacon until lightly brown. Add onion and cook until tender.
Add liquid, potatoes and seasonings.
Cook 15 minutes until potatoes are tender. Add milk and heat thoroughly, but don't boil.
Stir in chopped clams and warm gently, 2 to 5 minutes.

title: oatmeal blueberry muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add milk, egg and oil.
Mix until just moistened.
Fold in blueberries.
Fill 12 greased medium-size muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake in preheated 425° oven about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spinach casserole(serves 4)
directions: Saute spinach in olive oil with garlic.
Add salt and pepper. Cover and cook on medium heat until tender (about 10 minutes). Turn into casserole dish.
Cover with yogurt.
Serve.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: bessie's cream pie
directions: Mix pudding and milk together.
Add ice cream.
Pour into crust and top with Cool Whip.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease a shallow 3 1/2 to 4-quart baking dish.
Bring a large pot of boiling water to a boil.
Add macaroni and cook 10 to 12 minutes, until tender. Stir in broccoli, then immediately drain macaroni and broccoli in colander.
Squeeze cheese packets into same pot.
Stir in milk and soup until blended.
Stir in drained macaroni and broccoli, and then sausage. Put in prepared baking dish and cover.
Bake covered, 35 to 45 minutes until bubbly around edges.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place ingredients in casserole dish in layers.
Mix soup and water and pour over other ingredients.
Bake at 325° about 1 hour or until rice is done.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Heat oil in the wok and stir-fry the green peppers 1 to 2 minutes.
Then stir-fry the onions.
Push aside.
Stir-fry the steak 3 to 4 minutes.
Return the green peppers and onions to the steak in the wok.
Stir the cornstarch mixture, broth and soy sauce into the steak and peppers.
Heat until the sauce is thickened and clear.
Serve at once with rice.

title: easy, easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix the 3 ingredients and roll into small balls.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet and press the tops with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
For best results, let the cookies cool on the cookie sheet.
It only makes about 1 dozen cookies, but they are delicious and easy!

title: til's raisin pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour in unbaked crust and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chicken a la king
directions: In saucepan, cook onion and mushrooms in butter until onion is tender.
Blend in soup and milk; add remaining ingredients. Heat; stir now and then.
Serve over toast, biscuits, or mashed potatoes.
4 servings.

title: chili con ceso
directions: Brown hamburger with a little garlic salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients, except for cheese.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add cheese until melted.
Serve hot with Fritos.

title: italian rice
directions: Saute rice and garlic in the butter until golden brown.
Put in a 2-quart casserole.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
May be doubled.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add lemon juice and onion juice.
Chill until it starts to congeal.
Add whipped cream or Cool Whip, mayonnaise and cucumber; fold in lightly.
Congeal. Yields 8 servings.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix together. Drizzle over warm cookies.

title: healthy pot roast
directions: Trim fat from meat; slice into 3 sections.
Spray a Dutch oven with Pam and brown meat on all sides over medium-high heat.
Add stewed tomatoes, onion, garlic, bouillon, wine, basil and pepper. Simmer in 350° oven covered for 1 1/2 hours.
Cut potatoes in halves (or quarters if large) and add with carrots and celery to meat.
Simmer covered for an additional 40 to 50 minutes or until meat and vegetables are tender.
Remove meat and vegetables and keep warm.
Mix water and cornstarch and add to pan juices, cooking and stirring until thick.
Spoon gravy over meat and over vegetables and serve.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown rice in oil halfway.
Add onion and pepper and finish browning.
Dissolve chicken broth with water.
Add to rice, also tomato sauce and seasonings.
Add approximately 2 cups more water to cover rice.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let sit 5 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix ingredients all together.
Grease an oblong 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into squares when cooled.

title: old fashioned baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight; drain.
Add water to cover and soda. Bring to boil; drain.
Rinse with warm water; cover with more water.
Add salt and cook 45 minutes or until done.
Do not drain; add brown sugar and place bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cold pea salad
directions: Hand whisk mayonnaise, lemon juice and pepper until fluffy; add remaining ingredients and gently mix with 2 large spoons. Chill well before serving. (Measurement of all ingredients are subject to your own taste.)

title: squash dressing
directions: Cook squash and onion in enough water for simmering, about 1 1/2 cups until tender.
Drain, reserving 1 cup liquid.
Mix all ingredients lightly; place in 2-quart buttered casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until light golden brown.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: roquefort cheese balls
directions: Blend cheeses; add celery, onion, cayenne and salad dressing. Chill.
Form into small balls.
Roll in nuts.

title: coconut rum balls
directions: Mix vanilla wafers, coconut and pecans.
Add Eagle Brand milk and rum flavoring; mix well.
Chill for 4 hours.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Roll each ball in the powdered sugar.

title: hillbilly turkey stroganoff
directions: In a large saucepan, combine first 4 ingredients and heat until hot.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar.
Bring margarine, cocoa and Coke to a boil.
Mix boiled mixture with sifted ingredients, then add the buttermilk, baking soda, vanilla and eggs.
Stir in marshmallows. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: california salad
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and fold into vegetables. Chill.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Brown chicken.
Place in casserole.
Prepare onion soup mix and pour over chicken.
Add rice.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine eggs; add sugar, melted butter and allspice.
Fold in grated raw sweet potatoes.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until set.
Cool and serve with whipped topping.

title: weight watcher's dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute the first 3 ingredients in butter or oleo. Add the pimento, 1 stick melted oleo, soup, Cheez Whiz, chicken, spaghetti and pecans. Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: caramel bars
directions: Melt the caramels and cream in double boiler.
Mix the oatmeal, flour, brown sugar, baking soda and butter together. Take half of mixture; pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Don't overbake.
Drizzle caramel mixture over crust. Sprinkle the chocolate chips over the caramel mixture, then put rest of flour mixture over chips.
Bake another 5 minutes.
Cool.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Blend butter and flour together.
Add milk and boil until thickened.
Add seasonings and cheese and continue to heat, stirring constantly, until cheese is melted.

title: divinity(microwave)
directions: In a 3-quart bowl, cook sugar, syrup and water on High for 12 to 13 minutes (until it spins a fine thread).
Add salt to egg whites and beat on High until stiff.
Slowly pour syrup mixture in a thin stream into egg whites, beating constantly, until mixture loses its shine and thickens.
Stir in vanilla and nuts. Drop by teaspoons at once on waxed paper.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until creamy. Add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each addition. Sift dry ingredients. Add milk and sour cream to creamed mixture. Add lemon flavoring. Pour into a greased and floured tube pan. Bake in preheated oven at 300° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread each ingredient in order given in a greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake about 1 hour at 325°.

title: ham and cheese burrito
directions: On each burrito, spread 1 tablespoon sour cream and 1 or 2 tablespoons of salsa.
Put ham and cheese on top.
Roll burritos and cook for 10 minutes at 400°.

title: oatmeal filled cookies
directions: Mix together with hands, then roll like pie dough.
Then cut in rounds and put jelly in middle and fold over like a half moon shape.
Pack down around edge with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: apple brownies
directions: Mix in order given, adding all dry ingredients sifted together.
Bake in a 9 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: tony's tuna noodle casserole
directions: In medium saucepan, cook soup, cheese, milk and tuna until warm and cheese is melted.
Prepare and drain shells.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in 2 round cake pans.
Cool and cut each layer in half, making 4 layers.

title: crunchie cookies
directions: Spoon onto cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef and drain excess fat; cool well. Combine lettuce, onion, cheese and tomatoes. Mix well. Crush chips into bite-size pieces. Stir in chips and beef. Just before serving, combine Catalina and taco sauce. Pour over salad.
Mix well.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar and butter.
Add egg and flavoring.
Mix thoroughly. Measure flour by dipping method or by sifting.
Stir dry ingredients together and blend in.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Roll or roll into balls and press with glass greased and dipped in sugar on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: russian chicken
directions: Place breasts in scrambled egg mixture and dip in bread crumbs to coat.
In a skillet, brown in butter.
Place in a 9x13-inch baking dish and pour soup over breaded chicken.
Cover with tin foil and bake at 350° for 35-40 minutes.
Remove foil and sprinkle onions on top of chicken.
Bake, uncovered, for 10 more minutes.

title: beef oven ragout
directions: In a large casserole with a tight cover, combine wine, mushroom soup and onion soup mix.
Mix well.
Add meat.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.
Add carrots and onions.
Cook about 45 minutes.
If gravy is thin, add flour or cornstarch.
